{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878877361,"sessionID":"ses_2855f1963ffebvWWhivqMrbUXq","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa119d8001IGBnvsdrpuWhyO","messageID":"msg_d7aa10da7001E2dsQ8YkDc4M4A","sessionID":"ses_2855f1963ffebvWWhivqMrbUXq","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_6fbbcec156f448aa836cca7b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-030: Helm Chart 模板与 Values\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `manifests`  \n6: **Language:** YAML  \n7: **Size:** L  \n8: **Type:** Helm Chart implementation for AgentCube control plane components\n9: \n10: **Base Specs:** deployment/spec.md, deployment/design.md\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n15: \n16: ### REQ-030.1: Chart.yaml Metadata\n17: \n18: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement Chart.yaml with apiVersion v1, name agentcube, version 0.1.0, and appVersion 1.0.0.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Chart.yaml structure\n21: - **GIVEN** the Helm chart is initialized\n22: - **WHEN** Chart.yaml is created\n23: - **THEN** it SHALL contain:\n24:   - `apiVersion: v1`\n25:   - `name: agentcube`\n26:   - `description: A Helm chart for AgentCube`\n27:   - `version: 0.1.0`\n28:   - `appVersion: \"1.0.0\"`\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Chart metadata keywords\n31: - **GIVEN** Chart.yaml is created\n32: - **WHEN** metadata is defined\n33: - **THEN** keywords SHALL include: `agent`, `sandbox`, `kubernetes`, `volcano`\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Chart maintainers\n36: - **GIVEN** Chart.yaml is created\n37: - **WHEN** maintainers are defined\n38: - **THEN** maintainers SHALL include Volcano Authors with email `volcano-sh@googlegroups.com`\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Chart home and sources\n41: - **GIVEN** Chart.yaml is created\n42: - **WHEN** home and sources are defined\n43: - **THEN** they SHALL reference `https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ### REQ-030.2: values.yaml Configuration Tree\n48: \n49: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement values.yaml with complete configuration tree for Redis, Router, WorkloadManager, and Volcano Scheduler.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Redis configuration\n52: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n53: - **WHEN** redis configuration is defined\n54: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n55:   - `redis.addr: \"\"` (empty default, user must provide)\n56:   - `redis.password: \"\"` (empty default for non-auth Redis)\n57: \n58: #### Scenario: Router replicas and image\n59: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n60: - **WHEN** router configuration is defined\n61: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n62:   - `router.replicas: 1`\n63:   - `router.image.repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router`\n64:   - `router.image.pullPolicy: IfNotPresent`\n65:   - `router.image.tag: \"latest\"`\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Router service configuration\n68: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n69: - **WHEN** router service is defined\n70: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n71:   - `router.service.type: ClusterIP`\n72:   - `router.service.port: 8080`\n73:   - `router.service.targetPort: 8080`\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Router resources\n76: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n77: - **WHEN** router resources are defined\n78: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n79:   - `router.resources.limits.cpu: 500m`\n80:   - `router.resources.limits.memory: 512Mi`\n81:   - `router.resources.requests.cpu: 100m`\n82:   - `router.resources.requests.memory: 128Mi`\n83: \n84: #### Scenario: Router RBAC toggle\n85: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n86: - **WHEN** router.rbac configuration is defined\n87: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n88:   - `router.rbac.create: false` (disabled by default)\n89:   - `router.serviceAccountName: \"\"` (empty for auto-generated or default)\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager replicas and image\n92: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n93: - **WHEN** workloadmanager configuration is defined\n94: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n95:   - `workloadmanager.replicas: 1`\n96:   - `workloadmanager.image.repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager`\n97:   - `workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy: IfNotPresent`\n98:   - `workloadmanager.image.tag: \"latest\"`\n99: \n100: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager service configuration\n101: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n102: - **WHEN** workloadmanager service is defined\n103: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n104:   - `workloadmanager.service.type: ClusterIP`\n105:   - `workloadmanager.service.port: 8080`\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager resources\n108: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n109: - **WHEN** workloadmanager resources are defined\n110: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n111:   - `workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu: 500m`\n112:   - `workloadmanager.resources.limits.memory: 512Mi`\n113:   - `workloadmanager.resources.requests.cpu: 100m`\n114:   - `workloadmanager.resources.requests.memory: 128Mi`\n115: \n116: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager extraEnv\n117: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n118: - **WHEN** workloadmanager.extraEnv is defined\n119: - **THEN** it SHALL be an empty list `[]` for additional environment variables\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler enabled toggle\n122: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n123: - **WHEN** volcano.scheduler configuration is defined\n124: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n125:   - `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false` (disabled by default)\n126:   - `volcano.scheduler.replicas: 1`\n127:   - `volcano.scheduler.image.repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler`\n128:   - `volcano.scheduler.image.pullPolicy: IfNotPresent`\n129:   - `volcano.scheduler.image.tag: \"latest\"`\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: Image pull secrets\n132: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n133: - **WHEN** imagePullSecrets is defined\n134: - **THEN** it SHALL be an empty list `[]` by default\n135: \n136: #### Scenario: Name overrides\n137: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n138: - **WHEN** nameOverride and fullnameOverride are defined\n139: - **THEN** they SHALL be empty strings `\"\"` by default\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: Router extraEnv\n142: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n143: - **WHEN** router.extraEnv is defined\n144: - **THEN** it SHALL be an empty list `[]` for additional environment variables\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: Router config\n147: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n148: - **WHEN** router.config is defined\n149: - **THEN** it SHALL be an empty object `{}` for additional container configuration\n150: \n151: ---\n152: \n153: ### REQ-030.3: Workload Manager Deployment Template\n154: \n155: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement Workload Manager Deployment template with correct environment variables, probes, and resource configuration.\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: Workload Manager Deployment metadata\n158: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n159: - **WHEN** Workload Manager Deployment is created\n160: - **THEN** metadata SHALL include:\n161:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n162:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n163:   - Labels: `app.kubernetes.io/name: workloadmanager`, `app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}`\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: Workload Manager replicas from values\n166: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `workloadmanager.replicas: 2`\n167: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n168: - **THEN** `spec.replicas` SHALL be `2`\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: Workload Manager image from values\n171: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has custom image repository\n172: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n173: - **THEN** container image SHALL be `{{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.tag }}`\n174: \n175: #### Scenario: Workload Manager environment variables\n176: - **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n177: - **WHEN** container env is defined\n178: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n179:   - `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` from fieldRef `metadata.namespace`\n180:   - `REDIS_ADDR` from `{{ .Values.redis.addr }}`\n181:   - `REDIS_PASSWORD` from Secret `{{ .Release.Name }}-redis` key `password`\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: Workload Manager extraEnv injection\n184: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `workloadmanager.extraEnv` entries\n185: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n186: - **THEN** extraEnv entries SHALL be injected into container env\n187: \n188: #### Scenario: Workload Manager args\n189: - **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n190: - **WHEN** container args are defined\n191: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n192:   - `--port={{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}`\n193:   - `--runtime-class-name=` (empty)\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Workload Manager liveness probe\n196: - **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n197: - **WHEN** livenessProbe is defined\n198: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n199:   - `httpGet.path: /health`\n200:   - `httpGet.port: http`\n201:   - `initialDelaySeconds: 10`\n202:   - `periodSeconds: 10`\n203: \n204: #### Scenario: Workload Manager readiness probe\n205: - **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n206: - **WHEN** readinessProbe is defined\n207: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n208:   - `httpGet.path: /health`\n209:   - `httpGet.port: http`\n210:   - `initialDelaySeconds: 5`\n211:   - `periodSeconds: 5`\n212: \n213: #### Scenario: Workload Manager resources from values\n214: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `workloadmanager.resources` defined\n215: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n216: - **THEN** `resources` SHALL be rendered from values using `toYaml`\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: Workload Manager image pull secrets\n219: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `imagePullSecrets` entries\n220: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n221: - **THEN** `imagePullSecrets` SHALL be injected into pod spec\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: Workload Manager service account\n224: - **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n225: - **WHEN** serviceAccountName is defined\n226: - **THEN** it SHALL be `workloadmanager`\n227: \n228: #### Scenario: Workload Manager Service\n229: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n230: - **WHEN** Workload Manager Service is created\n231: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n232:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n233:   - `type: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.type }}`\n234:   - `port: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}`\n235:   - `targetPort: http`\n236:   - Selector: `app: workloadmanager`\n237: \n238: ---\n239: \n240: ### REQ-030.4: Router Deployment Template\n241: \n242: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement Router Deployment template with correct environment variables, probes, and WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL.\n243: \n244: #### Scenario: Router Deployment metadata\n245: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n246: - **WHEN** Router Deployment is created\n247: - **THEN** metadata SHALL include:\n248:   - `name: agentcube-router`\n249:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n250:   - Labels: `app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube-router`, `app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}`\n251: \n252: #### Scenario: Router replicas from values\n253: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `router.replicas: 3`\n254: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n255: - **THEN** `spec.replicas` SHALL be `3`\n256: \n257: #### Scenario: Router image from values\n258: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has custom router image\n259: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n260: - **THEN** container image SHALL be `{{ .Values.router.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.router.image.tag }}`\n261: \n262: #### Scenario: Router environment variables\n263: - **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n264: - **WHEN** container env is defined\n265: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n266:   - `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` from fieldRef `metadata.namespace`\n267:   - `REDIS_ADDR` from `{{ .Values.redis.addr }}`\n268:   - `REDIS_PASSWORD` from Secret `{{ .Release.Name }}-redis` key `password`\n269:   - `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL: \"http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\"`\n270: \n271: #### Scenario: Router extraEnv injection\n272: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `router.extraEnv` entries\n273: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n274: - **THEN** extraEnv entries SHALL be injected into container env\n275: \n276: #### Scenario: Router args\n277: - **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n278: - **WHEN** container args are defined\n279: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n280:   - `--port={{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}`\n281:   - `--debug`\n282: \n283: #### Scenario: Router liveness probe\n284: - **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n285: - **WHEN** livenessProbe is defined\n286: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n287:   - `httpGet.path: /health/live`\n288:   - `httpGet.port: http`\n289:   - `initialDelaySeconds: 1`\n290:   - `periodSeconds: 2`\n291: \n292: #### Scenario: Router readiness probe\n293: - **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n294: - **WHEN** readinessProbe is defined\n295: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n296:   - `httpGet.path: /health/ready`\n297:   - `httpGet.port: http`\n298:   - `initialDelaySeconds: 1`\n299:   - `periodSeconds: 2`\n300: \n301: #### Scenario: Router service account conditional\n302: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `router.serviceAccountName: \"custom-sa\"`\n303: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n304: - **THEN** `serviceAccountName` SHALL be `custom-sa`\n305: \n306: #### Scenario: Router service account empty\n307: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `router.serviceAccountName: \"\"`\n308: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n309: - **THEN** `serviceAccountName` SHALL NOT be set (use default)\n310: \n311: #### Scenario: Router Service\n312: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n313: - **WHEN** Router Service is created\n314: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n315:   - `name: agentcube-router`\n316:   - `type: {{ .Values.router.service.type }}`\n317:   - `port: {{ .Values.router.service.port }}`\n318:   - `targetPort: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}`\n319:   - Selector: `app: agentcube-router`\n320: \n321: ---\n322: \n323: ### REQ-030.5: Workload Manager RBAC\n324: \n325: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement Workload Manager RBAC resources (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding) with correct permissions.\n326: \n327: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ServiceAccount\n328: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n329: - **WHEN** Workload Manager ServiceAccount is created\n330: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n331:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n332:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n333:   - Labels: `app.kubernetes.io/name: workloadmanager`, `app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}`\n334: \n335: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole sandbox permissions\n336: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n337: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n338: - **THEN** it SHALL include rules for:\n339:   - `apiGroups: [\"agents.x-k8s.io\"]`, `resources: [\"sandboxes\"]`, `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n340: \n341: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole extension resources\n342: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n343: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n344: - **THEN** it SHALL include rules for:\n345:   - `apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]`\n346:   - `resources: [\"sandboxclaims\", \"sandboxtemplates\", \"sandboxwarmpools\"]`\n347:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n348: \n349: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole warm pool status\n350: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n351: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n352: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n353:   - `apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]`\n354:   - `resources: [\"sandboxwarmpools/status\"]`\n355:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]`\n356: \n357: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole CodeInterpreter permissions\n358: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n359: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n360: - **THEN** it SHALL include rules for:\n361:   - `apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]`\n362:   - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]`\n363:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n364:   - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters/status\"]`, `verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]`\n365:   - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters/finalizers\"]`, `verbs: [\"update\"]`\n366: \n367: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole AgentRuntime permissions\n368: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n369: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n370: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n371:   - `apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]`\n372:   - `resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]`\n373:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]`\n374:   - `resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\"]`\n375:   - `verbs: [\"update\", \"patch\"]`\n376: \n377: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole pod permissions\n378: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n379: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n380: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n381:   - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n382:   - `resources: [\"pods\"]`\n383:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]`\n384: \n385: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole token review\n386: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n387: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n388: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n389:   - `apiGroups: [\"authentication.k8s.io\"]`\n390:   - `resources: [\"tokenreviews\"]`\n391:   - `verbs: [\"create\"]`\n392: \n393: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole secret permissions\n394: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n395: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n396: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n397:   - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n398:   - `resources: [\"secrets\"]`\n399:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n400: \n401: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRoleBinding\n402: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n403: - **WHEN** ClusterRoleBinding is created\n404: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n405:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n406:   - Subject: `kind: ServiceAccount`, `name: workloadmanager`, `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n407:   - RoleRef: `kind: ClusterRole`, `name: workloadmanager`, `apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io`\n408: \n409: ---\n410: \n411: ### REQ-030.6: Router RBAC (Optional)\n412: \n413: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement optional Router RBAC resources controlled by `router.rbac.create` flag.\n414: \n415: #### Scenario: Router RBAC disabled by default\n416: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `router.rbac.create: false`\n417: - **WHEN** helm template is rendered\n418: - **THEN** Router RBAC resources SHALL NOT be created\n419: \n420: #### Scenario: Router RBAC enabled\n421: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `router.rbac.create: true`\n422: - **WHEN** helm template is rendered\n423: - **THEN** Router ServiceAccount, Role, and RoleBinding SHALL be created\n424: \n425: #### Scenario: Router ServiceAccount name\n426: - **GIVEN** Router RBAC is enabled\n427: - **WHEN** ServiceAccount is created\n428: - **THEN** name SHALL be `{{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}`\n429: \n430: #### Scenario: Router Role secret permissions\n431: - **GIVEN** Router RBAC is enabled\n432: - **WHEN** Role rules are defined\n433: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n434:   - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n435:   - `resources: [\"secrets\"]`\n436:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n437: \n438: #### Scenario: Router RoleBinding\n439: - **GIVEN** Router RBAC is enabled\n440: - **WHEN** RoleBinding is created\n441: - **THEN** it SHALL reference:\n442:   - Subject: ServiceAccount with default name\n443:   - RoleRef: Role with same name\n444: \n445: ---\n446: \n447: ### REQ-030.7: Volcano Agent Scheduler (Optional)\n448: \n449: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement optional Volcano Agent Scheduler resources controlled by `volcano.scheduler.enabled` flag.\n450: \n451: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler disabled by default\n452: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false`\n453: - **WHEN** helm template is rendered\n454: - **THEN** Volcano Scheduler resources SHALL NOT be created\n455: \n456: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler enabled\n457: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `volcano.scheduler.enabled: true`\n458: - **WHEN** helm template is rendered\n459: - **THEN** ServiceAccount, ConfigMap, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, Service, and Deployment SHALL be created\n460: \n461: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ServiceAccount\n462: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n463: - **WHEN** ServiceAccount is created\n464: - **THEN** name SHALL be `volcano-agent-scheduler`\n465: \n466: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ConfigMap\n467: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n468: - **WHEN** ConfigMap is created\n469: - **THEN** it SHALL include `agent-scheduler.conf` with:\n470:   - `actions: \"allocate\"`\n471:   - `tiers:` with `plugins: \"predicates,nodeorder\"`\n472: \n473: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole CRD permissions\n474: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n475: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n476: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n477:   - `apiGroups: [\"apiextensions.k8s.io\"]`\n478:   - `resources: [\"customresourcedefinitions\"]`\n479:   - `verbs: [\"create\", \"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"delete\"]`\n480: \n481: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole pod permissions\n482: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n483: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n484: - **THEN** it SHALL include comprehensive pod permissions:\n485:   - `pods`, `pods/status`, `pods/binding`, `pods/disruptionbudgets`\n486:   - `persistentvolumeclaims`, `persistentvolumes`\n487:   - `nodes`, `namespaces`, `services`, `replicationcontrollers`\n488: \n489: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole scheduling permissions\n490: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n491: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n492: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n493:   - `apiGroups: [\"scheduling.k8s.io\"]`\n494:   - `resources: [\"priorityclasses\"]`\n495:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]`\n496:   - `apiGroups: [\"scheduling.incubator.k8s.io\", \"scheduling.volcano.sh\"]`\n497:   - `resources: [\"podgroups\"]`\n498:   - `verbs: [\"list\", \"watch\", \"update\"]`\n499: \n500: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole storage permissions\n501: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n502: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n503: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n504:   - `apiGroups: [\"storage.k8s.io\"]`\n505:   - `resources: [\"storageclasses\", \"csinodes\", \"csidrivers\", \"csistoragecapacities\", \"volumeattachments\"]`\n506:   - `verbs: [\"list\", \"watch\"]`\n507: \n508: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole configmap permissions\n509: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n510: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n511: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n512:   - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n513:   - `resources: [\"configmaps\"]`\n514:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"delete\", \"update\"]`\n515: \n516: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRoleBinding\n517: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n518: - **WHEN** ClusterRoleBinding is created\n519: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n520:   - `name: volcano-agent-scheduler-role`\n521:   - Subject: `kind: ServiceAccount`, `name: volcano-agent-scheduler`\n522:   - RoleRef: `kind: ClusterRole`, `name: volcano-agent-scheduler`\n523: \n524: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler Service\n525: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n526: - **WHEN** Service is created\n527: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n528:   - `name: volcano-agent-scheduler-service`\n529:   - `port: 8080`, `targetPort: 8080`, `name: metrics`\n530:   - Annotations: `prometheus.io/scrape: \"true\"`, `prometheus.io/port: \"8080\"`\n531:   - Selector: `app: volcano-agent-scheduler`\n532: \n533: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler Deployment args\n534: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n535: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n536: - **THEN** container args SHALL include:\n537:   - `--scheduler-name=agent-scheduler`\n538:   - `--config=/config/agent-scheduler.conf`\n539: \n540: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler Deployment volumes\n541: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n542: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n543: - **THEN** it SHALL include volumes:\n544:   - `name: config`, `configMap.name: volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap`\n545:   - `name: empty`, `emptyDir: {}`\n546: \n547: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler security context\n548: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n549: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n550: - **THEN** container securityContext SHALL include:\n551:   - `runAsNonRoot: true`\n552:   - `runAsUser: 1000`\n553: \n554: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler replicas from values\n555: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `volcano.scheduler.replicas: 2`\n556: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n557: - **THEN** `spec.replicas` SHALL be `2`\n558: \n559: ---\n560: \n561: ### REQ-030.8: Redis Secret Template\n562: \n563: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement Redis Secret template to store Redis password.\n564: \n565: #### Scenario: Redis Secret creation\n566: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n567: - **WHEN** Redis Secret is created\n568: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n569:   - `name: {{ .Release.Name }}-redis`\n570:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n571:   - `type: Opaque`\n572: \n573: #### Scenario: Redis Secret data\n574: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `redis.password: \"mysecret\"`\n575: - **WHEN** Secret is rendered\n576: - **THEN** `stringData.password` SHALL be `\"mysecret\"`\n577: \n578: #### Scenario: Redis Secret labels\n579: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n580: - **WHEN** Secret labels are defined\n581: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n582:   - `app.kubernetes.io/name: redis`\n583:   - `app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}`\n584: \n585: ---\n586: \n587: ### REQ-030.9: CRD Files\n588: \n589: **Requirement:** The system SHALL include CRD files for agentruntimes and codeinterpreters.\n590: \n591: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime CRD existence\n592: - **GIVEN** the chart is installed\n593: - **WHEN** CRDs are applied\n594: - **THEN** `agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` SHALL be created\n595: \n596: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime CRD group and version\n597: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntime CRD is applied\n598: - **WHEN** CRD spec is validated\n599: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n600:   - `spec.group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n601:   - `spec.versions[0].name: v1alpha1`\n602: \n603: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter CRD existence\n604: - **GIVEN** the chart is installed\n605: - **WHEN** CRDs are applied\n606: - **THEN** `codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` SHALL be created\n607: \n608: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter CRD group and version\n609: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreter CRD is applied\n610: - **WHEN** CRD spec is validated\n611: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n612:   - `spec.group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n613:   - `spec.versions[0].name: v1alpha1`\n614: \n615: #### Scenario: CRD installation order\n616: - **GIVEN** helm install is run\n617: - **WHEN** chart is installed\n618: - **THEN** CRDs SHALL be installed before other resources\n619: \n620: ---\n621: \n622: ### REQ-030.10: .helmignore\n623: \n624: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement .helmignore file to exclude unnecessary files from chart packaging.\n625: \n626: #### Scenario: Git files ignored\n627: - **GIVEN** .helmignore is created\n628: - **WHEN** patterns are defined\n629: - **THEN** it SHALL include: `.git/`, `.gitignore`\n630: \n631: #### Scenario: Version control files ignored\n632: - **GIVEN** .helmignore is created\n633: - **WHEN** patterns are defined\n634: - **THEN** it SHALL include: `.bzr/`, `.bzrignore`, `.hg/`, `.hgignore`, `.svn/`\n635: \n636: #### Scenario: Temporary files ignored\n637: - **GIVEN** .helmignore is created\n638: - **WHEN** patterns are defined\n639: - **THEN** it SHALL include: `*.swp`, `*.bak`, `*.tmp`, `*.orig`, `*~`\n640: \n641: #### Scenario: IDE files ignored\n642: - **GIVEN** .helmignore is created\n643: - **WHEN** patterns are defined\n644: - **THEN** it SHALL include: `.project`, `.idea/`, `*.tmproj`, `.vscode/`\n645: \n646: #### Scenario: Test files ignored\n647: - **GIVEN** .helmignore is created\n648: - **WHEN** patterns are defined\n649: - **THEN** it SHALL include: `tests/`\n650: \n651: #### Scenario: Documentation files ignored\n652: - **GIVEN** .helmignore is created\n653: - **WHEN** patterns are defined\n654: - **THEN** it SHALL include: `*.md` but NOT `!README.md`\n655: \n656: ---\n657: \n658: ### REQ-030.11: Helm Lint and Template Validation\n659: \n660: **Requirement:** The system SHALL pass `helm lint` without errors and `helm template` shall generate valid YAML.\n661: \n662: #### Scenario: Helm lint passes\n663: - **GIVEN** chart structure is complete\n664: - **WHEN** `helm lint manifests/charts/base` is run\n665: - **THEN** it SHALL return no errors\n666: \n667: #### Scenario: Helm template generates valid YAML\n668: - **GIVEN** chart structure is complete\n669: - **WHEN** `helm template test manifests/charts/base` is run\n670: - **THEN** output SHALL be valid YAML that can be parsed\n671: \n672: #### Scenario: Helm template with custom values\n673: - **GIVEN** custom values file is provided\n674: - **WHEN** `helm template test manifests/charts/base -f custom-values.yaml` is run\n675: - **THEN** output SHALL reflect custom values overrides\n676: \n677: #### Scenario: Helm template with Volcano enabled\n678: - **GIVEN** `--set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true` is passed\n679: - **WHEN** `helm template` is run\n680: - **THEN** output SHALL include Volcano Scheduler resources\n681: \n682: #### Scenario: Helm template with Router RBAC enabled\n683: - **GIVEN** `--set router.rbac.create=true` is passed\n684: - **WHEN** `helm template` is run\n685: - **THEN** output SHALL include Router RBAC resources\n686: \n687: ---\n688: \n689: ### REQ-030.12: Multi-Environment Support\n690: \n691: **Requirement:** The system SHALL support multi-environment deployment through values overrides.\n692: \n693: #### Scenario: Development environment values\n694: - **GIVEN** development values file is provided\n695: - **WHEN** helm install is run with `-f values-dev.yaml`\n696: - **THEN** all components SHALL use development-appropriate settings (e.g., lower resources)\n697: \n698: #### Scenario: Production environment values\n699: - **GIVEN** production values file is provided\n700: - **WHEN** helm install is run with `-f values-prod.yaml`\n701: - **THEN** all components SHALL use production-appropriate settings (e.g., higher replicas, resources)\n702: \n703: #### Scenario: Region-specific Redis configuration\n704: - **GIVEN** different regions have different Redis addresses\n705: - **WHEN** helm install is run with `--set redis.addr=redis-region1.svc:6379`\n706: - **THEN** components SHALL connect to specified Redis address\n707: \n708: #### Scenario: Custom image repository override\n709: - **GIVEN** organization uses private registry\n710: - **WHEN** helm install is run with `--set router.image.repository=myregistry.com/router`\n711: - **THEN** Router SHALL use custom image repository\n712: \n713: ---\n714: \n715: ## Data Types\n716: \n717: ```yaml\n718: # values.yaml structure\n719: values:\n720:   imagePullSecrets: []\n721:   nameOverride: \"\"\n722:   fullnameOverride: \"\"\n723:   \n724:   redis:\n725:     addr: string       # Required: Redis address\n726:     password: string   # Optional: Redis password\n727:   \n728:   router:\n729:     replicas: int\n730:     image:\n731:       repository: string\n732:       pullPolicy: string\n733:       tag: string\n734:     service:\n735:       type: string\n736:       port: int\n737:       targetPort: int\n738:     resources:\n739:       limits:\n740:         cpu: string\n741:         memory: string\n742:       requests:\n743:         cpu: string\n744:         memory: string\n745:     config: object\n746:     extraEnv: []\n747:     serviceAccountName: string\n748:     rbac:\n749:       create: bool\n750:   \n751:   workloadmanager:\n752:     replicas: int\n753:     image:\n754:       repository: string\n755:       pullPolicy: string\n756:       tag: string\n757:     service:\n758:       type: string\n759:       port: int\n760:     resources:\n761:       limits:\n762:         cpu: string\n763:         memory: string\n764:       requests:\n765:         cpu: string\n766:         memory: string\n767:     extraEnv: []\n768:   \n769:   volcano:\n770:     scheduler:\n771:       enabled: bool\n772:       replicas: int\n773:       image:\n774:         repository: string\n775:         pullPolicy: string\n776:         tag: string\n777: ```\n778: \n779: ---\n780: \n781: ## File Structure\n782: \n783: ```\n784: manifests/charts/base/\n785: ├── Chart.yaml\n786: ├── values.yaml\n787: ├── .helmignore\n788: ├── crds/\n789: │   ├── agentruntime.yaml\n790: │   └── codeinterpreter.yaml\n791: └── templates/\n792:     ├── _helpers.tpl\n793:     ├── redis-secret.yaml\n794:     ├── workloadmanager.yaml\n795:     ├── agentcube-router.yaml\n796:     ├── rbac/\n797:     │   └── workloadmanager.yaml\n798:     ├── rbac-router.yaml\n799:     └── volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml\n800: ```\n801: \n802: ---\n803: \n804: ## Environment Variables\n805: \n806: | Variable | Component | Description | Source |\n807: |----------|-----------|-------------|--------|\n808: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | All | Namespace from downward API | fieldRef |\n809: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Router, WorkloadManager | Redis address | values.redis.addr |\n810: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Router, WorkloadManager | Redis password | Secret |\n811: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Router | Workload Manager URL | Constructed from values |\n812: \n813: ---\n814: \n815: ## Error Codes\n816: \n817: | Error | Exit Code | Message |\n818: |-------|-----------|---------|\n819: | Chart validation failure | 1 | `helm lint` failed: {detail} |\n820: | Template render failure | 1 | `helm template` failed: {detail} |\n821: | CRD installation failure | 1 | Failed to install CRD: {detail} |\n822: | Redis address not provided | 1 | `redis.addr` is required in values |\n823: | Invalid YAML syntax | 1 | YAML parse error in {file}: {detail} |\n824: \n825: ---\n826: \n827: ## Dependencies\n828: \n829: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n830: |---------|---------|---------|\n831: | Helm | ≥3.0 | Chart packaging and deployment |\n832: | Kubernetes | ≥1.21 | API compatibility |\n833: | Redis | Any | External dependency (session storage) |\n834: \n835: ---\n836: \n837: ## Acceptance Checklist\n838: \n839: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` — Chart metadata with correct apiVersion, name, version\n840: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` — Complete configuration tree for all components\n841: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` — Deployment + Service with correct env/probes\n842: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` — Deployment + Service with WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n843: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` — ServiceAccount + ClusterRole + ClusterRoleBinding\n844: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` — Conditional Router RBAC\n845: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` — Conditional Volcano Scheduler\n846: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/redis-secret.yaml` — Redis password Secret\n847: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/crds/agentruntime.yaml` — AgentRuntime CRD (existing, verify completeness)\n848: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/crds/codeinterpreter.yaml` — CodeInterpreter CRD (new)\n849: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/.helmignore` — Ignore patterns for packaging\n850: - [ ] `helm lint` passes without errors\n851: - [ ] `helm template` generates valid YAML\n852: - [ ] `helm install` succeeds in Kind cluster\n853: - [ ] Optional components render correctly when enabled/disabled\n854: - [ ] Values overrides work correctly for multi-environment support\n855: \n856: ---\n857: \n858: ## Open Questions\n859: \n860: 1. Should the chart support external Redis Operator integration?\n861: 2. Should monitoring and logging configurations be integrated into the chart?\n862: 3. Should multi-cluster deployment be supported through values configuration?\n863: 4. Should the chart include default values for development/testing environments?\n\n(End of file - total 863 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-030: Helm Chart 模板与 Values\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `manifests`  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** L  \n**Type:** Helm Chart implementation for AgentCube control plane components\n\n**Base Specs:** deployment/spec.md, deployment/design.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-030.1: Chart.yaml Metadata\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement Chart.yaml with apiVersion v1, name agentcube, version 0.1.0, and appVersion 1.0.0.\n\n#### Scenario: Chart.yaml structure","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775878877314,"end":1775878877358}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878877364,"sessionID":"ses_2855f1963ffebvWWhivqMrbUXq","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa1260e001O17IriiDtZDuSf","messageID":"msg_d7aa10da7001E2dsQ8YkDc4M4A","sessionID":"ses_2855f1963ffebvWWhivqMrbUXq","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_724e66e7211d4421aa68e601","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deployment Design\n2: \n3: Source tree: `/tmp/agentcube-ref` (reference clone). Paths below are relative to repository root unless noted.\n4: \n5: ## Chart.yaml\n6: \n7: | Field | Value |\n8: |--------|--------|\n9: | `apiVersion` | `v1` |\n10: | `name` | `agentcube` |\n11: | `description` | `A Helm chart for AgentCube` |\n12: | `version` | `0.1.0` |\n13: | `appVersion` | `1.0.0` |\n14: \n15: ## values.yaml — full key tree (type & default)\n16: \n17: | Path | Type | Default |\n18: |------|------|---------|\n19: | `imagePullSecrets` | array | `[]` |\n20: | `nameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |\n21: | `fullnameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |\n22: | `redis.addr` | string | `\"\"` |\n23: | `redis.password` | string | `\"\"` |\n24: | `router.replicas` | int | `1` |\n25: | `router.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router` |\n26: | `router.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n27: | `router.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n28: | `router.service.type` | string | `ClusterIP` |\n29: | `router.service.port` | int | `8080` |\n30: | `router.service.targetPort` | int | `8080` |\n31: | `router.resources.limits.cpu` | string | `500m` |\n32: | `router.resources.limits.memory` | string | `512Mi` |\n33: | `router.resources.requests.cpu` | string | `100m` |\n34: | `router.resources.requests.memory` | string | `128Mi` |\n35: | `router.config` | object | `{}` |\n36: | `router.extraEnv` | array | `[]` |\n37: | `router.serviceAccountName` | string | `\"\"` |\n38: | `router.rbac.create` | bool | `false` |\n39: | `workloadmanager.replicas` | int | `1` |\n40: | `workloadmanager.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager` |\n41: | `workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n42: | `workloadmanager.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n43: | `workloadmanager.service.type` | string | `ClusterIP` |\n44: | `workloadmanager.service.port` | int | `8080` |\n45: | `workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu` | string | `500m` |\n46: | `workloadmanager.resources.limits.memory` | string | `512Mi` |\n47: | `workloadmanager.resources.requests.cpu` | string | `100m` |\n48: | `workloadmanager.resources.requests.memory` | string | `128Mi` |\n49: | `workloadmanager.extraEnv` | array | `[]` |\n50: | `volcano.scheduler.enabled` | bool | `false` |\n51: | `volcano.scheduler.replicas` | int | `1` |\n52: | `volcano.scheduler.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler` |\n53: | `volcano.scheduler.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n54: | `volcano.scheduler.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n55: \n56: Comments in `values.yaml` state Redis settings “must be provided by the user during installation”; defaults are still empty strings.\n57: \n58: ## Template files (`manifests/charts/base/templates/`)\n59: \n60: ### `workloadmanager.yaml`\n61: \n62: | Kind | Name | Namespace | Notes |\n63: |------|------|-----------|--------|\n64: | `Deployment` | `workloadmanager` | `{{ .Release.Namespace }}` | `replicas`: `workloadmanager.replicas`; `serviceAccountName`: `workloadmanager`; optional `imagePullSecrets`; container `workloadmanager`; image `repository:tag`; `imagePullPolicy`; port `http` → `workloadmanager.service.port`; **env**: `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (fieldRef `metadata.namespace`), `REDIS_PASSWORD`, `REDIS_ADDR`, plus `workloadmanager.extraEnv`; **args**: `--port={{ workloadmanager.service.port }}`, `--runtime-class-name=` (empty); **resources**: from values; **liveness/readiness**: HTTP GET `/health` on service port, delays 10s/10s and 5s/5s |\n65: | `Service` | `workloadmanager` | release ns | `type`: `workloadmanager.service.type`; port & `targetPort`: `workloadmanager.service.port`; selector `app: workloadmanager` |\n66: \n67: ### `agentcube-router.yaml`\n68: \n69: | Kind | Name | Notes |\n70: |------|------|--------|\n71: | `Deployment` | `agentcube-router` | `replicas`: `router.replicas`; **conditional** `serviceAccountName` if `router.serviceAccountName` non-empty; optional `imagePullSecrets`; container `agentcube-router`; image from `router.image`; container port `router.service.targetPort`; **env**: `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (fieldRef), `REDIS_ADDR`, `REDIS_PASSWORD`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` = `http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ workloadmanager.service.port }}`, plus `router.extraEnv`; **args**: `--port={{ router.service.targetPort }}`, `--debug`; **resources** from values; **liveness** `/health/live`, **readiness** `/health/ready` on targetPort, 1s initial, 2s period |\n72: | `Service` | `agentcube-router` | `type` `router.service.type`; `port` `router.service.port`, `targetPort` `router.service.targetPort`; selector `app: agentcube-router` |\n73: \n74: ### `rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n75: \n76: | Kind | Name | Scope | Notes |\n77: |------|------|-------|--------|\n78: | `ServiceAccount` | `workloadmanager` | release namespace | — |\n79: | `ClusterRole` | `workloadmanager` | cluster | rules below |\n80: | `ClusterRoleBinding` | `workloadmanager` | cluster | binds `ClusterRole/workloadmanager` to `ServiceAccount/workloadmanager` in release namespace |\n81: \n82: ### `rbac-router.yaml`\n83: \n84: Rendered **only if** `router.rbac.create` is true.\n85: \n86: | Kind | Name pattern | Notes |\n87: |------|--------------|--------|\n88: | `ServiceAccount` | `{{ router.serviceAccountName \\| default \"agentcube-router\" }}` | release namespace |\n89: | `Role` | same as SA name | rules: `secrets` in `\"\"` apiGroup, full verb set `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n90: | `RoleBinding` | same | subject: SA above; `Role` ref same name |\n91: \n92: ### `volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n93: \n94: Rendered **only if** `volcano.scheduler.enabled`.\n95: \n96: Creates (in order in file): `ServiceAccount/volcano-agent-scheduler`; `ConfigMap/volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap` with key `agent-scheduler.conf` (actions `allocate`, tiers predicates/nodeorder); `ClusterRole/volcano-agent-scheduler` (large rule set — see RBAC section); `ClusterRoleBinding/volcano-agent-scheduler-role`; `Service/volcano-agent-scheduler-service` (port 8080 metrics annotations); `Deployment/volcano-agent-scheduler` with `replicas` from `volcano.scheduler.replicas`, image from values, args including `--scheduler-name=agent-scheduler`, security contexts, volumes for config + emptyDir.\n97: \n98: ## RBAC rules (exact apiGroups / resources / verbs)\n99: \n100: ### ClusterRole `workloadmanager`\n101: \n102: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n103: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n104: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxes` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n105: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxclaims` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n106: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxtemplates` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n107: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n108: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n109: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n110: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n111: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/finalizers` | `update` |\n112: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes` | `get,list,watch` |\n113: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes/status` | `update,patch` |\n114: | `\"\"` | `pods` | `get,list,watch` |\n115: | `authentication.k8s.io` | `tokenreviews` | `create` |\n116: | `\"\"` | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n117: \n118: ### Role `router` (optional)\n119: \n120: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n121: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n122: | `\"\"` | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n123: \n124: ### ClusterRole `volcano-agent-scheduler` (when enabled)\n125: \n126: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n127: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n128: | `apiextensions.k8s.io` | `customresourcedefinitions` | `create,get,list,watch,delete` |\n129: | `\"\"` | `events` | `create,list,watch,update,patch` |\n130: | `\"\"` | `pods` | `get,list,watch,patch,delete` |\n131: | `\"\"` | `pods/status` | `update` |\n132: | `\"\"` | `pods/binding` | `create` |\n133: | `\"\"` | `persistentvolumeclaims` | `list,watch,update` |\n134: | `\"\"` | `persistentvolumes` | `list,watch,update` |\n135: | `\"\"` | `namespaces,services,replicationcontrollers` | `list,watch,get` |\n136: | `\"\"` | `resourcequotas` | `list,watch` |\n137: | `\"\"` | `nodes` | `get,list,watch,update,patch` |\n138: | `storage.k8s.io` | `storageclasses,csinodes,csidrivers,csistoragecapacities,volumeattachments` | `list,watch` |\n139: | `policy` | `poddisruptionbudgets` | `list,watch` |\n140: | `scheduling.k8s.io` | `priorityclasses` | `get,list,watch` |\n141: | `scheduling.incubator.k8s.io`, `scheduling.volcano.sh` | `podgroups` | `list,watch,update` |\n142: | `\"\"` | `configmaps` | `get,list,watch,create,delete,update` |\n143: | `apps` | `daemonsets,replicasets,statefulsets` | `list,watch,get` |\n144: | `coordination.k8s.io` | `leases` | `get,create,update,watch` |\n145: | `resource.k8s.io` | `resourceclaims` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch` |\n146: | `resource.k8s.io` | `resourceclaims/status` | `update` |\n147: | `resource.k8s.io` | `deviceclasses,resourceslices` | `get,list,watch,create` |\n148: | `shard.volcano.sh` | `nodeshards` | `list,watch,get,update` |\n149: \n150: ## CRD definitions shipped (`manifests/charts/base/crds/`)\n151: \n152: | File | CRD `metadata.name` | group | versions | scope | Notes |\n153: |------|---------------------|-------|----------|-------|--------|\n154: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml` | `agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `v1alpha1` (served+storage); printer column Age | `Namespaced` | `openAPIV3Schema` includes root fields `apiVersion`, `kind`, `metadata`, `spec`, `status`. **spec.required**: `maxSessionDuration`, `podTemplate`, `sessionTimeout`, `targetPort`. **Key spec fields**: `maxSessionDuration` (string, default `8h`); `sessionTimeout` (string, default `15m`); `targetPort` (array of port objects: required `port`, `protocol` enum HTTP/HTTPS, optional `name`, `pathPrefix`); `podTemplate` (annotations, labels, nested `spec` = full PodSpec-shaped schema). **status**: conditions, etc. Annotation `controller-gen.kubebuilder.io/version: v0.17.2` |\n155: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` | `codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `v1alpha1` | `Namespaced` | **spec** includes `authMode` enum `picod|none` default `picod`; `maxSessionDuration` default `8h`; `sessionTimeout` default `15m`; `ports` (same TargetPort shape as above); `template` (image, command, args, env, resources, runtimeClassName, etc.); optional `warmPoolSize` int32. **spec.required**: `template`. **status**: `conditions`, `ready`; subresource `status`. Same controller-gen version annotation |\n156: \n157: ## Dockerfiles\n158: \n159: ### `docker/Dockerfile` (workloadmanager)\n160: \n161: | Stage | Base | Purpose |\n162: |-------|------|---------|\n163: | builder | `golang:1.24.9-alpine` | `WORKDIR /workspace`; copy `go.mod`/`go.sum`; `go mod download`; copy `cmd/`, `pkg/`; build `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=${TARGETOS} GOARCH=${TARGETARCH} go build -ldflags=\"-s -w\" -o workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager` with BuildKit cache mounts |\n164: | runtime | `alpine:3.19` | `apk add ca-certificates`; `WORKDIR /app`; copy binary; `adduser -D -u 1000 apiserver`; `USER apiserver`; `EXPOSE 8080`; `ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/workloadmanager\"]`; `CMD [\"--port=8080\"]` |\n165: \n166: Build args: `TARGETOS=linux`, `TARGETARCH` (implicit platform).\n167: \n168: ### `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n169: \n170: Same pattern as workloadmanager builder, plus `COPY client-go/ client-go/`; output binary `agentcube-router` from `./cmd/router`; runtime user `router` UID 1000; `CMD [\"--port=8080\", \"--debug\"]`.\n171: \n172: ### `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n173: \n174: | Stage | Base | Purpose |\n175: |-------|------|---------|\n176: | builder | `golang:1.24.4` | `WORKDIR /app`; copy mod files; download; `COPY . .`; build `picod` from `./cmd/picod` with `CGO_ENABLED=0` |\n177: | runtime | `ubuntu:24.04` | `apt-get install -y python3`; `WORKDIR /root/`; copy binary; **runs as root** (comment: chattr on pubkey + sandbox permissions); `ENTRYPOINT [\"./picod\"]` |\n178: \n179: ## Makefile — variables (key)\n180: \n181: | Variable | Default / definition |\n182: |----------|----------------------|\n183: | `HUB` | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh` |\n184: | `TAG` | `latest` |\n185: | `PROJECT_DIR` | directory of Makefile |\n186: | `GOBIN` | from `go env` |\n187: | `CONTAINER_TOOL` | `docker` |\n188: | `SHELL` | `/usr/bin/env bash -o pipefail` |\n189: | `LOCALBIN` | `$(shell pwd)/bin` |\n190: | `CONTROLLER_GEN` | `$(LOCALBIN)/controller-gen` |\n191: | `GOLANGCI_LINT` | `$(LOCALBIN)/golangci-lint` |\n192: | `CONTROLLER_TOOLS_VERSION` | `v0.17.2` |\n193: | `GOLANGCI_LINT_VERSION` | `v1.64.1` |\n194: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE` | `workloadmanager:latest` |\n195: | `ROUTER_IMAGE` | `agentcube-router:latest` |\n196: | `PICOD_IMAGE` | `picod:latest` |\n197: | `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `\"\"` |\n198: | `E2E_CLUSTER_NAME` | `agentcube-e2e` |\n199: | `AGENT_SANDBOX_REPO` | `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox.git` |\n200: | `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION` | `main` (Makefile comment; E2E script overrides — see CI design) |\n201: \n202: ## Makefile — targets\n203: \n204: | Target | Depends / notes |\n205: |--------|-----------------|\n206: | `all` | → `build` |\n207: | `help` | awk help from `##` comments |\n208: | `gen-crd` | `controller-gen`; `crd paths=./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...` → `manifests/charts/base/crds` |\n209: | `generate` | `controller-gen object` + `gen-crd` + `go mod tidy` |\n210: | `gen-client` | `bash hack/update-codegen.sh`; `go mod tidy` |\n211: | `gen-all` | `generate` + `gen-client` |\n212: | `gen-check` | `gen-all` then `git diff --exit-code` |\n213: | `build` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager` |\n214: | `build-agentd` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd` |\n215: | `build-router` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/agentcube-router ./cmd/router` |\n216: | `build-all` | `build` + `build-agentd` + `build-router` |\n217: | `run` | `go run ./cmd/workload-manager/main.go --port=8080 --ssh-username=sandbox --ssh-port=22` |\n218: | `run-local` | same with `--kubeconfig=${HOME}/.kube/config` |\n219: | `run-router` | `go run ./cmd/router/main.go --port=8080 --debug` |\n220: | `clean` | `rm -rf bin/` and root binaries |\n221: | `deps` | `go mod download`; `go mod tidy` |\n222: | `update-deps` | `go get -u ./...`; `go mod tidy` |\n223: | `test` | `go test -v ./...` |\n224: | `fmt` | `go fmt ./...` |\n225: | `vet` | `go vet ./...` |\n226: | `lint` | `$(GOLANGCI_LINT) run ./...` |\n227: | `gen-copyright` | `hack/update-copyright.sh` |\n228: | `install` | `build` + `sudo cp bin/workloadmanager /usr/local/bin/` |\n229: | `docker-build` | `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile -t $(WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE) .` |\n230: | `docker-buildx` | buildx linux/amd64,arm64 |\n231: | `docker-buildx-push` | requires `IMAGE_REGISTRY`; buildx `--push` |\n232: | `docker-push` | tag+push workloadmanager |\n233: | `kind-load` | `kind load docker-image $(WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE)` |\n234: | `docker-build-router` / `docker-buildx-router` / `docker-buildx-push-router` / `docker-push-router` / `kind-load-router` | same pattern for router image |\n235: | `docker-build-picod` / `docker-buildx-picod` / `docker-buildx-push-picod` / `docker-push-picod` | same for picod |\n236: | `controller-gen` / `golangci-lint` | download via `go-install-tool` macro |\n237: | `e2e` | `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` |\n238: | `e2e-clean` | `kind delete cluster --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)`; `rm -rf /tmp/agent-sandbox` |\n239: | `build-python-sdk` | copy `LICENSE` to `sdk-python`, `python3 -m build` in `sdk-python`, remove copied LICENSE |\n240: \n241: ## hack/ scripts\n242: \n243: | File | Purpose |\n244: |------|---------|\n245: | `hack/update-codegen.sh` | Runs `k8s.io/code-generator` **v0.34.1**: sources `kube_codegen.sh`, calls `kube::codegen::gen_client --with-watch --output-dir client-go --output-pkg github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go --boilerplate hack/boilerplate.go.txt --one-input-api runtime/v1alpha1` on `pkg/apis`; post-processes lister files with `sed` to append `.GroupResource()` for codeinterpreter/agentruntime resources |\n246: | `hack/update-copyright.sh` | Prepends Apache/Volcano boilerplate to `*.go` and `*.py` under git root (excluding vendor/venv) if missing “Copyright The Volcano Authors”; uses `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` / `hack/boilerplate.py.txt`; requires `sponge` (moreutils) |\n247: | `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` | Go file header template |\n248: | `hack/boilerplate.py.txt` | Python file header template |\n249: \n250: ## Helm / E2E reference command (from `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`)\n251: \n252: Illustrative install used in E2E:\n253: \n254: ```bash\n255: helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n256:   --namespace \"${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}\" \\\n257:   --create-namespace \\\n258:   --set redis.addr=\"redis.${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}.svc.cluster.local:6379\" \\\n259:   --set redis.password=\"\" \\\n260:   --set workloadmanager.image.repository=\"workloadmanager\" \\\n261:   --set workloadmanager.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n262:   --set-json 'workloadmanager.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\",\"value\":\"false\"},{\"name\":\"JWT_KEY_SECRET_NAMESPACE\",\"value\":\"agentcube\"}]' \\\n263:   --set router.image.repository=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n264:   --set router.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n265:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n266:   --set router.serviceAccountName=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n267:   --set-json 'router.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\",\"value\":\"false\"}]' \\\n268:   --wait\n269: ```\n270: \n271: Images are expected to be loaded into Kind with local names `workloadmanager:latest`, `agentcube-router:latest`, `picod:latest` after `make docker-build` variants.\n\n(End of file - total 271 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deployment Design\n\nSource tree: `/tmp/agentcube-ref` (reference clone). Paths below are relative to repository root unless noted.\n\n## Chart.yaml\n\n| Field | Value |\n|--------|--------|\n| `apiVersion` | `v1` |\n| `name` | `agentcube` |\n| `description` | `A Helm chart for AgentCube` |\n| `version` | `0.1.0` |\n| `appVersion` | `1.0.0` |\n\n## values.yaml — full key tree (type & default)\n\n| Path | Type | Default |\n|------|------|---------|\n| `imagePullSecrets` | array | `[]` |\n| `nameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/design.md","time":{"start":1775878877329,"end":1775878877362}}}}
