{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775878877403,"sessionID":"ses_2855f1963ffebvWWhivqMrbUXq","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa130ca001ng6SQ7h5QXA2Jk","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7aa10da7001E2dsQ8YkDc4M4A","sessionID":"ses_2855f1963ffebvWWhivqMrbUXq","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":20089,"input":6,"output":361,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":4236,"read":15486}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775878882975,"sessionID":"ses_2855f1963ffebvWWhivqMrbUXq","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa1469c001VUPbpdPLDsBSew","messageID":"msg_d7aa130fa00173mF08DeDfS7en","sessionID":"ses_2855f1963ffebvWWhivqMrbUXq","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878888349,"sessionID":"ses_2855f1963ffebvWWhivqMrbUXq","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa153fc001V3iC39iA0eEtBu","messageID":"msg_d7aa130fa00173mF08DeDfS7en","sessionID":"ses_2855f1963ffebvWWhivqMrbUXq","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_717a4f1a08c2445690b5055a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Design: AR-005 Sandbox Creation Processor\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This document describes the technical implementation for the Sandbox processor module within `pkg/workloadmanager`. The processor handles creation and lifecycle management of sandbox environments using Kubernetes custom resources.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Component Structure\n10: \n11: ```\n12: pkg/workloadmanager/\n13: ├── processor/\n14: │   ├── sandbox_processor.go      # Main processor implementation\n15: │   ├── sandbox_processor_test.go # Unit tests\n16: │   └── interface.go              # Processor interface definition\n17: ├── types/\n18: │   └── sandbox.go                # Sandbox data structures\n19: └── config/\n20:     └── sandbox_config.go         # Configuration structures\n21: ```\n22: \n23: ### Integration Points\n24: \n25: - **Client-go**: Uses generated typed client for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n26: - **Informers**: Watches `CodeInterpreter` and `AgentRuntime` resources\n27: - **Listers**: Provides cached read access to resources\n28: \n29: ## Data Structures\n30: \n31: ### Sandbox Processor\n32: \n33: ```go\n34: type SandboxProcessor struct {\n35:     client       runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n36:     informer     cache.SharedIndexInformer\n37:     lister       runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterLister\n38:     config       *SandboxConfig\n39:     eventHandler cache.ResourceEventHandlerRegistration\n40: }\n41: \n42: type SandboxConfig struct {\n43:     DefaultNamespace     string\n44:     ResourceTimeout      time.Duration\n45:     DefaultCPURequest    string\n46:     DefaultMemoryRequest string\n47:     AllowedRuntimes      []string\n48: }\n49: ```\n50: \n51: ### Sandbox Context\n52: \n53: ```go\n54: type SandboxContext struct {\n55:     Name         string\n56:     Namespace    string\n57:     RuntimeType  string\n58:     Owner        string\n59:     Labels       map[string]string\n60:     Annotations  map[string]string\n61:     Resources    v1.ResourceRequirements\n62: }\n63: ```\n64: \n65: ## API Contracts\n66: \n67: ### Processor Interface\n68: \n69: ```go\n70: type Processor interface {\n71:     Create(ctx context.Context, sandbox *SandboxContext) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n72:     Update(ctx context.Context, sandbox *SandboxContext) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n73:     Delete(ctx context.Context, name, namespace string) error\n74:     Get(ctx context.Context, name, namespace string) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n75:     Watch(ctx context.Context, namespace string) (watch.Interface, error)\n76: }\n77: ```\n78: \n79: ### Create Operation\n80: \n81: **Input**: `SandboxContext` with required fields: `Name`, `Namespace`, `RuntimeType`\n82: \n83: **Output**: `*CodeInterpreter` or error\n84: \n85: **Behavior**:\n86: 1. Validate sandbox context (required fields, allowed runtime types)\n87: 2. Check for existing sandbox with same name\n88: 3. Construct `CodeInterpreter` object with proper labels/annotations\n89: 4. Apply resource quotas from config\n90: 5. Call `client.CodeInterpreters(namespace).Create()`\n91: 6. Return created resource or error\n92: \n93: ### Update Operation\n94: \n95: **Input**: `SandboxContext` with `Name`, `Namespace`, and fields to update\n96: \n97: **Output**: `*CodeInterpreter` or error\n98: \n99: **Behavior**:\n100: 1. Fetch existing `CodeInterpreter`\n101: 2. Apply updates (resources, labels, annotations)\n102: 3. Call `client.CodeInterpreters(namespace).Update()`\n103: 4. Return updated resource\n104: \n105: ### Delete Operation\n106: \n107: **Input**: `name`, `namespace`\n108: \n109: **Output**: error\n110: \n111: **Behavior**:\n112: 1. Call `client.CodeInterpreters(namespace).Delete()`\n113: 2. Handle `NotFound` errors gracefully\n114: \n115: ## Error Handling\n116: \n117: ### Error Types\n118: \n119: ```go\n120: var (\n121:     ErrSandboxNotFound     = errors.New(\"sandbox not found\")\n122:     ErrSandboxExists       = errors.New(\"sandbox already exists\")\n123:     ErrInvalidRuntime      = errors.New(\"invalid runtime type\")\n124:     ErrValidationFailed    = errors.New(\"sandbox validation failed\")\n125:     ErrCreateTimeout       = errors.New(\"sandbox creation timeout\")\n126: )\n127: ```\n128: \n129: ### Error Wrapping\n130: \n131: All errors wrapped with context using `fmt.Errorf(\"context: %w\", err)`.\n132: \n133: ### Retry Strategy\n134: \n135: - Transient errors: 3 retries with exponential backoff (100ms, 200ms, 400ms)\n136: - `TooManyRequests`: Respect `Retry-After` header\n137: - Permanent errors: Return immediately without retry\n138: \n139: ## Testing Strategy\n140: \n141: ### Unit Tests\n142: \n143: **File**: `processor/sandbox_processor_test.go`\n144: \n145: **Test Cases**:\n146: 1. `TestCreateSandbox_Success` - Valid sandbox creation\n147: 2. `TestCreateSandbox_InvalidRuntime` - Rejected runtime type\n148: 3. `TestCreateSandbox_AlreadyExists` - Duplicate creation\n149: 4. `TestUpdateSandbox_Success` - Resource update\n150: 5. `TestDeleteSandbox_Success` - Normal deletion\n151: 6. `TestDeleteSandbox_NotFound` - Idempotent delete\n152: 7. `TestGetSandbox_Success` - Retrieve existing sandbox\n153: \n154: ### Test Fixtures\n155: \n156: ```go\n157: func newTestSandboxContext(name, runtime string) *SandboxContext {\n158:     return &SandboxContext{\n159:         Name:        name,\n160:         Namespace:   \"default\",\n161:         RuntimeType: runtime,\n162:         Resources: v1.ResourceRequirements{\n163:             Requests: v1.ResourceList{\n164:                 v1.ResourceCPU:    resource.MustParse(\"100m\"),\n165:                 v1.ResourceMemory: resource.MustParse(\"128Mi\"),\n166:             },\n167:         },\n168:     }\n169: }\n170: ```\n171: \n172: ### Mock Setup\n173: \n174: ```go\n175: func newTestProcessor(client runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface) *SandboxProcessor {\n176:     return &SandboxProcessor{\n177:         client: client,\n178:         config: &SandboxConfig{\n179:             DefaultNamespace: \"default\",\n180:             ResourceTimeout:  30 * time.Second,\n181:             AllowedRuntimes:  []string{\"python\", \"nodejs\", \"go\"},\n182:         },\n183:     }\n184: }\n185: ```\n186: \n187: ### Integration Tests\n188: \n189: **File**: `processor/sandbox_processor_integration_test.go`\n190: \n191: Tests against real Kubernetes cluster (kind) using `envtest`:\n192: 1. Full lifecycle (create → update → delete)\n193: 2. Concurrent operations\n194: 3. Resource quota enforcement\n195: \n196: ## Implementation Notes\n197: \n198: ### Resource Naming\n199: \n200: CodeInterpreter resources follow pattern: `sandbox-{owner}-{uuid}`\n201: \n202: ### Labels\n203: \n204: Standard labels applied to all sandboxes:\n205: - `app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube`\n206: - `app.kubernetes.io/component: sandbox`\n207: - `agentcube.volcano.sh/owner: <owner>`\n208: - `agentcube.volcano.sh/runtime: <runtime-type>`\n209: \n210: ### Annotations\n211: \n212: - `agentcube.volcano.sh/created-at: <RFC3339>`\n213: - `agentcube.volcano.sh/last-updated: <RFC3339>`\n214: \n215: ### Timeout Handling\n216: \n217: Creation uses context with timeout from `config.ResourceTimeout`. Watch for resource to reach `Ready` phase within timeout window.\n218: \n219: ---\n220: \n221: # Design: AR-014 Valkey Storage Implementation\n222: \n223: ## Overview\n224: \n225: This document describes the technical implementation of the session store for AgentCube, supporting both Redis and Valkey backends. The store persists sandbox metadata keyed by session ID, with sorted set indexes for expiry and last-activity tracking to enable garbage collection.\n226: \n227: ## Architecture\n228: \n229: ```\n230: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n231: │                     Application Layer                        │\n232: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n233:                             │\n234:                             ▼\n235: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n236: │                    store.Singleton                           │\n237: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n238: │  │ Storage() → Store (sync.Once initialization)         │   │\n239: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n240: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n241:                             │\n242:             ┌───────────────┴───────────────┐\n243:             │ STORE_TYPE (case-insensitive) │\n244:             ▼                               ▼\n245: ┌───────────────────────┐       ┌───────────────────────┐\n246: │    redisStore         │       │    valkeyStore        │\n247: │  - *redisv9.Client    │       │  - valkey.Client      │\n248: │  - sessionPrefix      │       │  - sessionPrefix      │\n249: │  - expiryIndexKey     │       │  - expiryIndexKey     │\n250: │  - lastActivityIndex  │       │  - lastActivityIndex  │\n251: └───────────────────────┘       └───────────────────────┘\n252:             │                               │\n253:             ▼                               ▼\n254: ┌───────────────────────┐       ┌───────────────────────┐\n255: │   Redis Server        │       │   Valkey Server       │\n256: │   - session:{id}      │       │   - session:{id}      │\n257: │   - session:expiry    │       │   - session:expiry    │\n258: │   - session:last_activity│    │   - session:last_activity│\n259: └───────────────────────┘       └───────────────────────┘\n260: ```\n261: \n262: ## Data Structures\n263: \n264: ### SandboxInfo (Primary Document)\n265: \n266: **Package:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types`\n267: \n268: ```go\n269: type SandboxInfo struct {\n270:     Kind             string              `json:\"kind\"`\n271:     SandboxID        string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n272:     SandboxNamespace string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n273:     Name             string              `json:\"name\"`\n274:     EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n275:     SessionID        string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n276:     CreatedAt        time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n277:     ExpiresAt        time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n278:     Status           string              `json:\"status\"`\n279: }\n280: \n281: type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n282:     Path     string `json:\"path\"`\n283:     Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n284:     Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n285: }\n286: ```\n287: \n288: **Storage Format:** JSON-serialized string stored at key `session:{sessionID}`\n289: \n290: ### Index Structures\n291: \n292: | Index | Type | Key | Member | Score |\n293: |-------|------|-----|--------|-------|\n294: | Expiry | Sorted Set | `session:expiry` | sessionID | `ExpiresAt.Unix()` |\n295: | Last Activity | Sorted Set | `session:last_activity` | sessionID | `lastActivity.Unix()` |\n296: \n297: ## Store Interface Contract\n298: \n299: **Package:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store`\n300: \n301: ```go\n302: type Store interface {\n303:     Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n304:     GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n305:     StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n306:     UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n307:     DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n308:     ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n309:     ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n310:     UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n311:     Close() error\n312: }\n313: ```\n314: \n315: ### Error Handling\n316: \n317: ```go\n318: var ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n319: ```\n320: \n321: | Error Condition | Error Value |\n322: |-----------------|-------------|\n323: | Key does not exist on GET | `ErrNotFound` |\n324: | Session missing on UpdateSessionLastActivity | `ErrNotFound` |\n325: | SET XX fails on UpdateSandbox (key not exists) | `key not exists` error |\n326: | Nil sandbox on StoreSandbox | validation error |\n327: | Zero ExpiresAt on StoreSandbox | validation error |\n328: \n329: ## Implementation Details\n330: \n331: ### Singleton Pattern (singleton.go)\n332: \n333: ```go\n334: var (\n335:     initStoreOnce = &sync.Once{}\n336:     provider      Store\n337: )\n338: \n339: func Storage() Store {\n340:     initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)\n341:     return provider\n342: }\n343: \n344: func initStore() error {\n345:     storeType := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"STORE_TYPE\"))\n346:     if storeType == \"\" {\n347:         storeType = redisStoreType\n348:     }\n349:     \n350:     switch storeType {\n351:     case redisStoreType:\n352:         provider = newRedisStore()\n353:     case valkeyStoreType:\n354:         provider = newValkeyStore()\n355:     default:\n356:         return fmt.Errorf(\"unsupported store type: %s\", storeType)\n357:     }\n358:     return nil\n359: }\n360: ```\n361: \n362: ### Redis Implementation (store_redis.go)\n363: \n364: #### Connection Options\n365: \n366: ```go\n367: func makeRedisOptions() (*redisv9.Options, error) {\n368:     redisAddr := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_ADDR\")\n369:     if redisAddr == \"\" {\n370:         return nil, errors.New(\"REDIS_ADDR is required\")\n371:     }\n372:     \n373:     redisPassword := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD\")\n374:     passwordRequired := true\n375:     if v := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"); strings.ToLower(v) == \"false\" {\n376:         passwordRequired = false\n377:     }\n378:     \n379:     if passwordRequired && redisPassword == \"\" {\n380:         return nil, errors.New(\"REDIS_PASSWORD is required\")\n381:     }\n382:     \n383:     return &redisv9.Options{\n384:         Addr:     redisAddr,\n385:         Password: redisPassword,\n386:     }, nil\n387: }\n388: ```\n389: \n390: #### Key Operations\n391: \n392: | Operation | Redis Commands | Notes |\n393: |-----------|----------------|-------|\n394: | Ping | `PING` → expect \"PONG\" | Health check |\n395: | GetSandboxBySessionID | `GET session:{id}` | Return `ErrNotFound` on Nil |\n396: | StoreSandbox | Pipeline: `SETNX`, `ZADD expiry`, `ZADD last_activity` | Atomic batch |\n397: | UpdateSandbox | `SET key value XX` | Only update value, not indexes |\n398: | DeleteSandboxBySessionID | Pipeline: `DEL`, `ZREM expiry`, `ZREM last_activity` | Full cleanup |\n399: | ListExpiredSandboxes | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix} LIMIT 0 limit` + pipeline GETs | Skip missing keys |\n400: | ListInactiveSandboxes | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity -inf {before.Unix} LIMIT 0 limit` + pipeline GETs | Skip missing keys |\n401: | UpdateSessionLastActivity | `EXISTS key` → `ZADD last_activity` | Verify key exists first |\n402: \n403: ### Valkey Implementation (store_valkey.go)\n404: \n405: #### Connection Options\n406: \n407: ```go\n408: func makeValkeyOptions() (*valkey.ClientOption, error) {\n409:     valkeyAddr := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_ADDR\")\n410:     if valkeyAddr == \"\" {\n411:         return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")\n412:     }\n413:     \n414:     valkeyPassword := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD\")\n415:     passwordRequired := true\n416:     if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"); strings.ToLower(v) == \"false\" {\n417:         passwordRequired = false\n418:     }\n419:     \n420:     if passwordRequired && valkeyPassword == \"\" {\n421:         return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD is required\")\n422:     }\n423:     \n424:     opt := &valkey.ClientOption{\n425:         InitAddress: strings.Split(valkeyAddr, \",\"),\n426:         Password:    valkeyPassword,\n427:     }\n428:     \n429:     if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE\"); v != \"\" {\n430:         if disable, err := strconv.ParseBool(v); err == nil && disable {\n431:             opt.DisableCache = true\n432:         }\n433:     }\n434:     \n435:     if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE\"); v != \"\" {\n436:         if force, err := strconv.ParseBool(v); err == nil && force {\n437:             opt.ForceSingleClient = true\n438:         }\n439:     }\n440:     \n441:     if opt.DisableCache || opt.ForceSingleClient {\n442:         klog.V(4).Infof(\"Valkey options: DisableCache=%v, ForceSingleClient=%v\", \n443:             opt.DisableCache, opt.ForceSingleClient)\n444:     }\n445:     \n446:     return opt, nil\n447: }\n448: ```\n449: \n450: #### Key Operations\n451: \n452: | Operation | Valkey API | Notes |\n453: |-----------|------------|-------|\n454: | Ping | `B().Ping()` → string \"PONG\" | Health check |\n455: | GetSandboxBySessionID | `B().Get().Key(key)` | `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound` |\n456: | StoreSandbox | `DoMulti`: SETNX, ZADD expiry, ZADD last_activity | Atomic batch |\n457: | UpdateSandbox | `SET ... XX` | Response must be \"OK\" |\n458: | DeleteSandboxBySessionID | `DoMulti`: DEL, ZREM expiry, ZREM last_activity | Full cleanup |\n459: | ListExpiredSandboxes | `Zrangebyscore` with Min(\"-inf\"), Max(before.Unix), Limit(0, limit) | Use MGET for batch load |\n460: | ListInactiveSandboxes | Same on last_activity key | MGET requires same slot |\n461: | UpdateSessionLastActivity | `Exists` → int64 must be 1, then `Zadd` | Verify existence first |\n462: \n463: #### MGET Optimization Note\n464: \n465: The `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` function uses single `MGET` for batch loading. This assumes all `session:{id}` keys are in the same cluster slot, which should be ensured through deployment configuration (e.g., hash tags or single-node deployment).\n466: \n467: ## Environment Configuration\n468: \n469: ### Common Variables\n470: \n471: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n472: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n473: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Provider selection (`redis` or `valkey`), case-insensitive |\n474: \n475: ### Redis-Specific Variables\n476: \n477: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n478: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n479: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | - | Redis server address (host:port) |\n480: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Yes* | - | Password for authentication |\n481: | `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Set to `false` to disable password requirement |\n482: \n483: \\* Required unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` (case-insensitive)\n484: \n485: ### Valkey-Specific Variables\n486: \n487: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n488: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n489: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | - | Comma-separated list of Valkey addresses |\n490: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes* | - | Password for authentication |\n491: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Set to `false` to disable password requirement |\n492: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` to disable client-side caching |\n493: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` to force single-client mode |\n494: \n495: ## API Contracts\n496: \n497: ### StoreSandbox Validation\n498: \n499: ```go\n500: func (s *redisStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxInfo *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n501:     if sandboxInfo == nil {\n502:         return errors.New(\"sandbox cannot be nil\")\n503:     }\n504:     if sandboxInfo.ExpiresAt.IsZero() {\n505:         return errors.New(\"expiresAt cannot be zero\")\n506:     }\n507:     // ... proceed with atomic pipeline\n508: }\n509: ```\n510: \n511: ### UpdateSandbox Semantics\n512: \n513: - **Only updates the JSON value** using `SET key value XX`\n514: - **Does NOT modify** expiry or last-activity sorted set entries\n515: - **Fails if key does not exist** (Redis: returns false; Valkey: response != \"OK\")\n516: \n517: ### List Operations - Orphan Handling\n518: \n519: Both `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `ListInactiveSandboxes` tolerate orphan ZSET entries (session IDs in the index without corresponding JSON documents):\n520: \n521: ```go\n522: // Skip entries where GET returns nil/empty\n523: if result == nil || result == \"\" {\n524:     continue // orphan ZSET member, skip\n525: }\n526: ```\n527: \n528: ### UpdateSessionLastActivity Preconditions\n529: \n530: 1. Session ID must be non-empty\n531: 2. If `at` is zero time, use `time.Now()`\n532: 3. **Verify session key exists** before ZADD\n533: 4. Return `ErrNotFound` if key does not exist\n534: \n535: ## Testing Strategy\n536: \n537: ### Unit Tests\n538: \n539: **File:** `pkg/store/store_redis_test.go`, `pkg/store/store_valkey_test.go`\n540: \n541: | Test Case | Description |\n542: |-----------|-------------|\n543: | `TestPing_Success` | Verify PING returns PONG |\n544: | `TestGetSandboxBySessionID_NotFound` | Verify `ErrNotFound` on missing key |\n545: | `TestStoreSandbox_NilRejected` | Verify nil sandbox validation |\n546: | `TestStoreSandbox_ZeroExpiresAtRejected` | Verify zero time validation |\n547: | `TestStoreSandbox_Atomicity` | Verify all three commands execute or fail together |\n548: | `TestUpdateSandbox_MissingKey` | Verify error when key doesn't exist |\n549: | `TestDeleteSandboxBySessionID_FullCleanup` | Verify DEL + ZREM operations |\n550: | `TestListExpiredSandboxes_OrphanTolerance` | Verify missing keys are skipped |\n551: | `TestUpdateSessionLastActivity_MissingSession` | Verify `ErrNotFound` on missing key |\n552: | `TestStorage_Singleton` | Verify sync.Once behavior with concurrent calls |\n553: \n554: ### Integration Tests\n555: \n556: **File:** `pkg/store/integration_test.go`\n557: \n558: | Test Case | Backend | Description |\n559: |-----------|---------|-------------|\n560: | `TestIntegration_StoreAndGet` | Redis, Valkey | Full store → get cycle |\n561: | `TestIntegration_ExpiryIndex` | Redis, Valkey | Verify ZSET score is correct |\n562: | `TestIntegration_LastActivityIndex` | Redis, Valkey | Verify activity tracking |\n563: | `TestIntegration_GC_ListExpired` | Redis, Valkey | Garbage collection query |\n564: | `TestIntegration_GC_ListInactive` | Redis, Valkey | Inactivity detection |\n565: | `TestIntegration_ConcurrentAccess` | Redis, Valkey | Concurrent store/update operations |\n566: \n567: ### Test Fixtures\n568: \n569: ```go\n570: func newTestSandbox(sessionID string, expiresAt time.Time) *types.SandboxInfo {\n571:     return &types.SandboxInfo{\n572:         Kind:             \"sandbox\",\n573:         SandboxID:        \"sandbox-123\",\n574:         SandboxNamespace: \"default\",\n575:         Name:             \"test-sandbox\",\n576:         SessionID:        sessionID,\n577:         CreatedAt:        time.Now(),\n578:         ExpiresAt:        expiresAt,\n579:         Status:           \"running\",\n580:         EntryPoints:      []types.SandboxEntryPoint{},\n581:     }\n582: }\n583: ```\n584: \n585: ## Dependencies\n586: \n587: ```go\n588: import (\n589:     // Redis client\n590:     \"github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\"\n591:     \n592:     // Valkey client\n593:     \"github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\"\n594:     \n595:     // Logging\n596:     \"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n597:     \n598:     // Internal types\n599:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n600: )\n601: ```\n602: \n603: ## File Structure\n604: \n605: ```\n606: pkg/store/\n607: ├── store.go                    # Store interface definition\n608: ├── singleton.go                # Storage() singleton with sync.Once\n609: ├── store_redis.go              # Redis implementation\n610: ├── store_redis_test.go         # Redis unit tests\n611: ├── store_valkey.go             # Valkey implementation\n612: ├── store_valkey_test.go        # Valkey unit tests\n613: ├── integration_test.go         # Integration tests (both backends)\n614: └── errors.go                   # ErrNotFound and other package errors\n615: ```\n616: \n617: ## Regeneration\n618: \n619: Client code regeneration (if Kubernetes client updates are needed):\n620: \n621: ```bash\n622: make gen-client  # Runs hack/update-codegen.sh\n623: ```\n624: \n625: Uses `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 with `--with-watch` flag.\n626: \n627: ---\n628: \n629: # Design: AR-017 PicoD JWT Middleware\n630: \n631: ## Overview\n632: \n633: This document describes the technical implementation of JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD HTTP server. The middleware validates JWT tokens on incoming requests and injects validated claims into the request context for downstream handlers.\n634: \n635: ## Architecture\n636: \n637: ### Component Placement\n638: \n639: ```\n640: ┌─────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐\n641: │   Client    │────▶│  PicoD HTTP  │────▶│ JWT Middle- │────▶│   Handler   │\n642: │  (with JWT) │     │   Server     │     │   ware      │     │  (Business) │\n643: └─────────────┘     └──────────────┘     └─────────────┘     └─────────────┘\n644: ```\n645: \n646: ### Package Structure\n647: \n648: ```\n649: pkg/picod/\n650: ├── jwt/\n651: │   ├── middleware.go      # HTTP middleware handler\n652: │   ├── validator.go       # JWT validation logic\n653: │   ├── claims.go          # Custom claims structure\n654: │   ├── config.go          # Configuration types\n655: │   └── error.go           # Error types\n656: ├── server.go              # PicoD server integration\n657: └── ...\n658: ```\n659: \n660: ### Dependencies\n661: \n662: - `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` - JWT parsing and validation\n663: - Standard library: `net/http`, `context`, `errors`, `fmt`, `strings`\n664: \n665: ## Data Structures\n666: \n667: ### Config\n668: \n669: ```go\n670: type Config struct {\n671:     // SigningKey is the secret key for HMAC verification\n672:     SigningKey []byte\n673:     \n674:     // SigningMethod is the signing algorithm (default: \"HS256\")\n675:     SigningMethod string\n676:     \n677:     // SkipPaths are paths that bypass JWT validation\n678:     SkipPaths map[string]bool\n679:     \n680:     // TokenLookup defines where to extract token from\n681:     // Format: \"header:<name>\" or \"query:<name>\"\n682:     TokenLookup string\n683:     \n684:     // ContextKey is the key to store claims in context\n685:     ContextKey string\n686:     \n687:     // ExpiryMax is the maximum allowed token expiry duration\n688:     ExpiryMax time.Duration\n689: }\n690: ```\n691: \n692: ### Claims\n693: \n694: ```go\n695: type Claims struct {\n696:     jwt.RegisteredClaims\n697:     \n698:     // Custom claims\n699:     UserID    string   `json:\"user_id,omitempty\"`\n700:     Namespace string   `json:\"namespace,omitempty\"`\n701:     Roles     []string `json:\"roles,omitempty\"`\n702: }\n703: ```\n704: \n705: ### Middleware\n706: \n707: ```go\n708: type Middleware struct {\n709:     config  *Config\n710:     keyFunc jwt.Keyfunc\n711:     parser  *jwt.Parser\n712: }\n713: ```\n714: \n715: ### Context Keys\n716: \n717: ```go\n718: type contextKey string\n719: \n720: const (\n721:     ClaimsKey contextKey = \"jwt_claims\"\n722: )\n723: ```\n724: \n725: ## API Contracts\n726: \n727: ### Middleware Constructor\n728: \n729: ```go\n730: func New(config Config) (*Middleware, error)\n731: ```\n732: \n733: **Behavior**:\n734: 1. Validate config (SigningKey required, valid SigningMethod)\n735: 2. Set defaults (SigningMethod=\"HS256\", TokenLookup=\"header:Authorization\")\n736: 3. Create keyFunc for HMAC verification\n737: 4. Configure parser with allowed methods\n738: 5. Return middleware instance or error\n739: \n740: ### HTTP Handler\n741: \n742: ```go\n743: func (m *Middleware) Handler(next http.Handler) http.Handler\n744: ```\n745: \n746: **Behavior**:\n747: 1. Check if request path is in SkipPaths\n748: 2. Extract token from header/query per TokenLookup\n749: 3. Parse and validate JWT\n750: 4. On success: inject claims to context, call next handler\n751: 5. On failure: return 401/403 with JSON error response\n752: \n753: ### Context Extraction\n754: \n755: ```go\n756: func GetClaims(ctx context.Context) (*Claims, bool)\n757: ```\n758: \n759: **Behavior**:\n760: 1. Extract claims from context using ClaimsKey\n761: 2. Return claims and true if present, nil and false otherwise\n762: \n763: ### Error Response Format\n764: \n765: ```go\n766: type Error struct {\n767:     Code    string `json:\"code\"`\n768:     Message string `json:\"message\"`\n769: }\n770: ```\n771: \n772: **Standard Error Codes**:\n773: | Code | HTTP Status | Description |\n774: |------|-------------|-------------|\n775: | `JWT_MISSING` | 401 | No token provided |\n776: | `JWT_INVALID` | 401 | Token format/structure invalid |\n777: | `JWT_EXPIRED` | 401 | Token has expired |\n778: | `JWT_SIGNATURE_INVALID` | 401 | Signature verification failed |\n779: | `JWT_EXPIRY_EXCEEDED` | 401 | Token expiry exceeds maximum allowed |\n780: \n781: ## Implementation Details\n782: \n783: ### Token Extraction\n784: \n785: ```go\n786: func (m *Middleware) extractToken(r *http.Request) (string, error) {\n787:     parts := strings.SplitN(m.config.TokenLookup, \":\", 2)\n788:     if len(parts) != 2 {\n789:         return \"\", errors.New(\"invalid token lookup format\")\n790:     }\n791:     \n792:     switch parts[0] {\n793:     case \"header\":\n794:         auth := r.Header.Get(parts[1])\n795:         if auth == \"\" {\n796:             return \"\", ErrTokenMissing\n797:         }\n798:         // Strip \"Bearer \" prefix if present\n799:         return strings.TrimPrefix(auth, \"Bearer \"), nil\n800:         \n801:     case \"query\":\n802:         token := r.URL.Query().Get(parts[1])\n803:         if token == \"\" {\n804:             return \"\", ErrTokenMissing\n805:         }\n806:         return token, nil\n807:         \n808:     default:\n809:         return \"\", errors.New(\"unsupported token lookup type\")\n810:     }\n811: }\n812: ```\n813: \n814: ### Validation Flow\n815: \n816: ```go\n817: func (m *Middleware) validate(tokenString string) (*Claims, error) {\n818:     token, err := m.parser.ParseWithClaims(tokenString, &Claims{}, m.keyFunc)\n819:     if err != nil {\n820:         if errors.Is(err, jwt.ErrTokenExpired) {\n821:             return nil, ErrTokenExpired\n822:         }\n823:         if strings.Contains(err.Error(), \"signature\") {\n824:             return nil, ErrSignatureInvalid\n825:         }\n826:         return nil, ErrTokenInvalid\n827:     }\n828:     \n829:     claims, ok := token.Claims.(*Claims)\n830:     if !ok || !token.Valid {\n831:         return nil, ErrTokenInvalid\n832:     }\n833:     \n834:     // Check max expiry\n835:     if m.config.ExpiryMax > 0 && claims.ExpiresAt != nil {\n836:         if time.Until(claims.ExpiresAt.Time) > m.config.ExpiryMax {\n837:             return nil, ErrExpiryExceeded\n838:         }\n839:     }\n840:     \n841:     return claims, nil\n842: }\n843: ```\n844: \n845: ### HTTP Error Response\n846: \n847: ```go\n848: func writeError(w http.ResponseWriter, statusCode int, code, message string) {\n849:     w.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n850:     w.WriteHeader(statusCode)\n851:     json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(Error{Code: code, Message: message})\n852: }\n853: ```\n854: \n855: ## Error Handling\n856: \n857: ### Error Types\n858: \n859: ```go\n860: var (\n861:     ErrTokenMissing     = errors.New(\"jwt: token missing\")\n862:     ErrTokenInvalid     = errors.New(\"jwt: token invalid\")\n863:     ErrTokenExpired     = errors.New(\"jwt: token expired\")\n864:     ErrSignatureInvalid = errors.New(\"jwt: signature invalid\")\n865:     ErrExpiryExceeded   = errors.New(\"jwt: token expiry exceeds maximum\")\n866: )\n867: ```\n868: \n869: ### HTTP Response Codes\n870: \n871: | Scenario | Status | Response Body |\n872: |----------|--------|---------------|\n873: | Missing token | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_MISSING\",\"message\":\"Authorization token required\"}` |\n874: | Invalid format | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_INVALID\",\"message\":\"Invalid token format\"}` |\n875: | Expired token | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_EXPIRED\",\"message\":\"Token has expired\"}` |\n876: | Bad signature | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_SIGNATURE_INVALID\",\"message\":\"Invalid token signature\"}` |\n877: | Expiry exceeded | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_EXPIRY_EXCEEDED\",\"message\":\"Token expiry exceeds maximum allowed\"}` |\n878: \n879: ## Testing Strategy\n880: \n881: ### Unit Tests\n882: \n883: **File**: `jwt/middleware_test.go`\n884: \n885: ```go\n886: // Test middleware construction\n887: - TestNew_ValidConfig\n888: - TestNew_MissingSigningKey\n889: - TestNew_InvalidSigningMethod\n890: \n891: // Test token extraction\n892: - TestExtractToken_Header\n893: - TestExtractToken_Query\n894: - TestExtractToken_BearerPrefix\n895: - TestExtractToken_Missing\n896: \n897: // Test validation\n898: - TestValidateToken_ValidToken\n899: - TestValidateToken_ExpiredToken\n900: - TestValidateToken_InvalidSignature\n901: - TestValidateToken_MalformedToken\n902: - TestValidateToken_ExpiryExceeded\n903: \n904: // Test handler\n905: - TestMiddleware_SkipPath\n906: - TestMiddleware_HeaderExtraction\n907: - TestMiddleware_QueryExtraction\n908: - TestMiddleware_ContextInjection\n909: - TestMiddleware_UnauthorizedResponse\n910: ```\n911: \n912: ### Test Helpers\n913: \n914: **File**: `jwt/test_helpers.go`\n915: \n916: ```go\n917: // GenerateTestToken creates a signed JWT for testing\n918: func GenerateTestToken(claims *Claims, key []byte, expiry time.Duration) (string, error)\n919: \n920: // MockHTTPHandler returns a simple handler for testing\n921: func MockHTTPHandler(statusCode int) http.HandlerFunc\n922: \n923: // NewTestRequest creates an HTTP request with optional JWT\n924: func NewTestRequest(token, path, method string) *http.Request\n925: ```\n926: \n927: ### Integration Tests\n928: \n929: **File**: `jwt/integration_test.go`\n930: \n931: ```go\n932: // Full request flow tests\n933: - TestFullRequestFlow_WithValidJWT\n934: - TestFullRequestFlow_WithExpiredJWT\n935: - TestFullRequestFlow_WithoutJWT\n936: - TestFullRequestFlow_WithSkipPath\n937: - TestFullRequestFlow_CustomClaims\n938: ```\n939: \n940: ### Test Fixtures\n941: \n942: ```go\n943: func newTestConfig() Config {\n944:     return Config{\n945:         SigningKey:  []byte(\"test-secret-key\"),\n946:         SigningMethod: \"HS256\",\n947:         SkipPaths:   map[string]bool{\"/health\": true, \"/public\": true},\n948:         TokenLookup: \"header:Authorization\",\n949:         ContextKey:  \"claims\",\n950:         ExpiryMax:   24 * time.Hour,\n951:     }\n952: }\n953: \n954: func newTestClaims(userID, namespace string, roles []string) *Claims {\n955:     return &Claims{\n956:         RegisteredClaims: jwt.RegisteredClaims{\n957:             ExpiresAt: jwt.NewNumericDate(time.Now().Add(time.Hour)),\n958:             IssuedAt:  jwt.NewNumericDate(time.Now()),\n959:             Subject:   userID,\n960:         },\n961:         UserID:    userID,\n962:         Namespace: namespace,\n963:         Roles:     roles,\n964:     }\n965: }\n966: ```\n967: \n968: ## Security Considerations\n969: \n970: 1. **Key Management**: SigningKey should be loaded from environment variables or secret store, never hardcoded\n971: 2. **Algorithm Restriction**: Explicitly set allowed signing methods in parser to prevent algorithm confusion attacks\n972: 3. **Token Expiry**: Enforce reasonable expiry validation via ExpiryMax (default 24h)\n973: 4. **Path Whitelisting**: Default-deny approach; only paths in SkipPaths are public\n974: 5. **Constant-Time Comparison**: Use hmac.Equal for signature verification (handled by jwt library)\n975: \n976: ## Environment Configuration\n977: \n978: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n979: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n980: | `PICOD_JWT_SIGNING_KEY` | Yes | - | Secret key for HMAC verification |\n981: | `PICOD_JWT_SIGNING_METHOD` | No | `HS256` | Signing algorithm (HS256, HS384, HS512) |\n982: | `PICOD_JWT_SKIP_PATHS` | No | - | Comma-separated list of paths to skip |\n983: | `PICOD_JWT_TOKEN_LOOKUP` | No | `header:Authorization` | Token extraction location |\n984: | `PICOD_JWT_EXPIRY_MAX` | No | `24h` | Maximum allowed token expiry duration |\n985: \n986: ## File Structure\n987: \n988: ```\n989: pkg/picod/jwt/\n990: ├── config.go          # Configuration types and defaults\n991: ├── claims.go          # Claims structure\n992: ├── middleware.go      # HTTP middleware implementation\n993: ├── validator.go       # JWT validation logic\n994: ├── error.go           # Error types and messages\n995: ├── test_helpers.go    # Test utilities\n996: ├── config_test.go     # Configuration tests\n997: ├── middleware_test.go # Middleware unit tests\n998: └── integration_test.go # Integration tests\n999: ```\n\n(End of file - total 999 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Design: AR-005 Sandbox Creation Processor\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation for the Sandbox processor module within `pkg/workloadmanager`. The processor handles creation and lifecycle management of sandbox environments using Kubernetes custom resources.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Structure\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── processor/\n│   ├── sandbox_processor.go      # Main processor implementation\n│   ├── sandbox_processor_test.go # Unit tests\n│   └── interface.go              # Processor interface definition\n├── types/\n│   └── sandbox.go                # Sandbox data structures\n└── config/\n    └── sandbox_config.go         # Configuration structures","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775878888332,"end":1775878888346}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878888365,"sessionID":"ses_2855f1963ffebvWWhivqMrbUXq","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa1501b001HiCDGS8BHznsUq","messageID":"msg_d7aa130fa00173mF08DeDfS7en","sessionID":"ses_2855f1963ffebvWWhivqMrbUXq","type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"toolu_a3d5b8449d9f4014920859bf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"ls -la /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/charts/base/","description":"List base chart directory"},"output":"total 12\ndrwxr-xr-x 3 root root 4096 Apr 11 00:37 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 3 root root 4096 Apr 11 00:37 ..\ndrwxr-xr-x 2 root root 4096 Apr 11 00:46 crds\n","metadata":{"output":"total 12\ndrwxr-xr-x 3 root root 4096 Apr 11 00:37 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 3 root root 4096 Apr 11 00:37 ..\ndrwxr-xr-x 2 root root 4096 Apr 11 00:46 crds\n","exit":0,"description":"List base chart directory","truncated":false},"title":"List base chart directory","time":{"start":1775878888327,"end":1775878888364}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878888370,"sessionID":"ses_2855f1963ffebvWWhivqMrbUXq","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa15931001Mnrd3N8eZSgHmp","messageID":"msg_d7aa130fa00173mF08DeDfS7en","sessionID":"ses_2855f1963ffebvWWhivqMrbUXq","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_dcd6d9786237469f9a489edf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Design: AR-019 CLI Binary Entry Points\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This document describes the technical implementation for 4 CLI binaries in the agentcube project. These tools provide command-line interfaces for managing agentcube resources and interacting with the Kubernetes API.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Binary Structure\n10: \n11: ```\n12: cmd/\n13: ├── agentd/                      # Kubernetes controller (existing)\n14: │   └── main.go\n15: ├── agentcube/                   # Main CLI - resource management\n16: │   └── main.go\n17: ├── agentcube-admin/             # Admin CLI - cluster administration\n18: │   └── main.go\n19: ├── agentcube-shell/             # Interactive shell - sandbox access\n20: │   └── main.go\n21: └── agentcube-proxy/             # API proxy - local port forwarding\n22:     └── main.go\n23: ```\n24: \n25: ### Module Dependencies\n26: \n27: - **client-go**: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`\n28:   - Typed clients for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n29:   - Informers for watching resources\n30:   - Listers for cached read access\n31: - **controller-runtime**: Shared utilities for config, logging\n32: - **cobra**: CLI framework (all binaries)\n33: \n34: ## Data Structures\n35: \n36: ### agentcube (Main CLI)\n37: \n38: ```go\n39: type CLI struct {\n40:     clientset     versioned.Interface\n41:     informerFactory informers.SharedInformerFactory\n42:     namespace     string\n43:     outputFormat  string\n44: }\n45: \n46: type SandboxOptions struct {\n47:     Name           string\n48:     Namespace      string\n49:     RuntimeType    string\n50:     CPURequest     string\n51:     MemoryRequest  string\n52:     Labels         map[string]string\n53:     Annotations    map[string]string\n54:     Timeout        time.Duration\n55: }\n56: \n57: type RuntimeOptions struct {\n58:     Name          string\n59:     Namespace     string\n60:     Spec          runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec\n61:     Timeout       time.Duration\n62: }\n63: ```\n64: \n65: ### agentcube-admin (Admin CLI)\n66: \n67: ```go\n68: type AdminCLI struct {\n69:     clientset     versioned.Interface\n70:     kubeClient    kubernetes.Interface\n71:     config        *rest.Config\n72: }\n73: \n74: type QuotaConfig struct {\n75:     Namespace      string\n76:     DefaultCPU     string\n77:     DefaultMemory  string\n78:     MaxCPU         string\n79:     MaxMemory      string\n80:     MaxSandboxes   int64\n81: }\n82: \n83: type ClusterConfig struct {\n84:     AllowedRuntimes []string\n85:     DefaultNamespace string\n86:     EnableMonitoring bool\n87: }\n88: ```\n89: \n90: ### agentcube-shell (Interactive Shell)\n91: \n92: ```go\n93: type Shell struct {\n94:     clientset     versioned.Interface\n95:     kubeClient    kubernetes.Interface\n96:     restClient    *rest.RESTClient\n97:     sandboxName   string\n98:     namespace     string\n99:     shellType     string  // bash, sh, zsh\n100: }\n101: \n102: type SessionConfig struct {\n103:     Timeout        time.Duration\n104:     IdleTimeout    time.Duration\n105:     HistoryFile    string\n106:     MaxHistory     int\n107: }\n108: ```\n109: \n110: ### agentcube-proxy (API Proxy)\n111: \n112: ```go\n113: type Proxy struct {\n114:     clientset     versioned.Interface\n115:     localPort     int\n116:     targetPort    int\n117:     namespace     string\n118:     resourceType  string  // agentruntime, codeinterpreter\n119:     resourceName  string\n120: }\n121: \n122: type ProxyConfig struct {\n123:     ListenAddress  string\n124:     ListenPort     int\n125:     TLS            bool\n126:     TLSCert        string\n127:     TLSKey         string\n128:     AuthToken      string\n129: }\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ## API Contracts\n133: \n134: ### agentcube Commands\n135: \n136: ```bash\n137: # Sandbox management\n138: agentcube sandbox create <name> [--runtime=<type>] [--namespace=<ns>] [--cpu=<req>] [--memory=<req>]\n139: agentcube sandbox get <name> [--namespace=<ns>] [-o=json|yaml]\n140: agentcube sandbox list [--namespace=<ns>] [-l=<labels>]\n141: agentcube sandbox delete <name> [--namespace=<ns>] [--force]\n142: agentcube sandbox watch <name> [--namespace=<ns>] [--timeout=<duration>]\n143: \n144: # Runtime management\n145: agentcube runtime create <name> --spec=<file> [--namespace=<ns>]\n146: agentcube runtime get <name> [--namespace=<ns>] [-o=json|yaml]\n147: agentcube runtime list [--namespace=<ns>]\n148: agentcube runtime update <name> --spec=<file>\n149: agentcube runtime delete <name> [--namespace=<ns>]\n150: \n151: # Utility\n152: agentcube version\n153: agentcube completion <bash|zsh|fish>\n154: agentcube config view\n155: agentcube config set <key>=<value>\n156: ```\n157: \n158: ### agentcube-admin Commands\n159: \n160: ```bash\n161: # Quota management\n162: agentcube-admin quota set <namespace> --cpu=<default> --memory=<default> --max-cpu=<max> --max-memory=<max>\n163: agentcube-admin quota get <namespace>\n164: agentcube-admin quota list\n165: \n166: # Cluster configuration\n167: agentcube-admin config get\n168: agentcube-admin config update --file=<config>\n169: \n170: # Health & diagnostics\n171: agentcube-admin health check\n172: agentcube-admin health report [-o=json|yaml]\n173: \n174: # Cleanup\n175: agentcube-admin cleanup idle [--older-than=<duration>]\n176: agentcube-admin cleanup failed [--namespace=<ns>]\n177: ```\n178: \n179: ### agentcube-shell Commands\n180: \n181: ```bash\n182: # Interactive access\n183: agentcube-shell connect <sandbox-name> [--namespace=<ns>] [--shell=<type>]\n184: agentcube-shell exec <sandbox-name> <command> [--namespace=<ns>]\n185: agentcube-shell cp <sandbox-name>:<src> <dst> [--namespace=<ns>]\n186: agentcube-shell port-forward <sandbox-name> <local-port>:<remote-port>\n187: \n188: # Session management\n189: agentcube-shell sessions list\n190: agentcube-shell sessions kill <session-id>\n191: ```\n192: \n193: ### agentcube-proxy Commands\n194: \n195: ```bash\n196: # API proxy\n197: agentcube-proxy start --resource=<type>/<name> --port=<local-port> [--namespace=<ns>]\n198: agentcube-proxy start --api-server --port=<local-port>\n199: \n200: # Status\n201: agentcube-proxy status\n202: agentcube-proxy stop\n203: ```\n204: \n205: ## Implementation Details\n206: \n207: ### Shared Libraries\n208: \n209: ```go\n210: // pkg/cliutil/config.go\n211: type ClientConfig struct {\n212:     Kubeconfig   string\n213:     Context      string\n214:     Namespace    string\n215:     APIServer    string\n216:     Token        string\n217:     Timeout      time.Duration\n218: }\n219: \n220: func LoadConfig() (*ClientConfig, error)\n221: func (c *ClientConfig) GetClientset() (versioned.Interface, error)\n222: func (c *ClientConfig) GetInformerFactory() (informers.SharedInformerFactory, error)\n223: \n224: // pkg/cliutil/output.go\n225: func PrintObject(obj runtime.Object, format string) error\n226: func PrintTable(rows [][]string, headers []string) error\n227: func PrintStatus(status string, format string) error\n228: \n229: // pkg/cliutil/validation.go\n230: func ValidateSandboxName(name string) error\n231: func ValidateRuntimeType(rt string, allowed []string) error\n232: func ValidateResourceQuantity(q string) error\n233: ```\n234: \n235: ### agentcube - Main CLI\n236: \n237: ```go\n238: // cmd/agentcube/main.go\n239: func main() {\n240:     rootCmd := &cobra.Command{\n241:         Use:   \"agentcube\",\n242:         Short: \"AgentCube CLI for managing agent runtimes and sandboxes\",\n243:     }\n244:     \n245:     rootCmd.PersistentFlags().String(\"kubeconfig\", \"\", \"path to kubeconfig\")\n246:     rootCmd.PersistentFlags().String(\"namespace\", \"default\", \"namespace\")\n247:     rootCmd.PersistentFlags().StringP(\"output\", \"o\", \"table\", \"output format\")\n248:     \n249:     rootCmd.AddCommand(sandboxCmd, runtimeCmd, configCmd, versionCmd)\n250:     \n251:     if err := rootCmd.Execute(); err != nil {\n252:         os.Exit(1)\n253:     }\n254: }\n255: \n256: // cmd/agentcube/sandbox.go\n257: func newSandboxCreateCmd() *cobra.Command {\n258:     opts := &SandboxOptions{}\n259:     cmd := &cobra.Command{\n260:         Use:   \"create <name>\",\n261:         Args:  cobra.ExactArgs(1),\n262:         RunE: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) error {\n263:             opts.Name = args[0]\n264:             return runSandboxCreate(opts)\n265:         },\n266:     }\n267:     cmd.Flags().StringVar(&opts.RuntimeType, \"runtime\", \"jupyter\", \"runtime type\")\n268:     cmd.Flags().StringVar(&opts.CPURequest, \"cpu\", \"100m\", \"CPU request\")\n269:     cmd.Flags().StringVar(&opts.MemoryRequest, \"memory\", \"256Mi\", \"memory request\")\n270:     return cmd\n271: }\n272: \n273: func runSandboxCreate(opts *SandboxOptions) error {\n274:     cfg, err := cliutil.LoadConfig()\n275:     if err != nil {\n276:         return err\n277:     }\n278:     \n279:     clientset, err := cfg.GetClientset()\n280:     if err != nil {\n281:         return err\n282:     }\n283:     \n284:     // Construct CodeInterpreter object\n285:     ci := &runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter{\n286:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n287:             Name:      opts.Name,\n288:             Namespace: opts.Namespace,\n289:             Labels:    opts.Labels,\n290:         },\n291:         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterSpec{\n292:             RuntimeType: opts.RuntimeType,\n293:             Resources: v1.ResourceRequirements{\n294:                 Requests: v1.ResourceList{\n295:                     v1.ResourceCPU:    resource.MustParse(opts.CPURequest),\n296:                     v1.ResourceMemory: resource.MustParse(opts.MemoryRequest),\n297:                 },\n298:             },\n299:         },\n300:     }\n301:     \n302:     result, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(opts.Namespace).Create(\n303:         cmd.Context(), ci, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n304:     if err != nil {\n305:         return err\n306:     }\n307:     \n308:     return cliutil.PrintObject(result, cfg.OutputFormat)\n309: }\n310: ```\n311: \n312: ### agentcube-admin - Admin CLI\n313: \n314: ```go\n315: // cmd/agentcube-admin/main.go\n316: func main() {\n317:     rootCmd := &cobra.Command{\n318:         Use:   \"agentcube-admin\",\n319:         Short: \"AgentCube Admin CLI for cluster administration\",\n320:     }\n321:     \n322:     rootCmd.PersistentFlags().String(\"kubeconfig\", \"\", \"path to kubeconfig\")\n323:     rootCmd.PersistentFlags().String(\"context\", \"\", \"kubeconfig context\")\n324:     \n325:     rootCmd.AddCommand(quotaCmd, configCmd, healthCmd, cleanupCmd)\n326:     \n327:     if err := rootCmd.Execute(); err != nil {\n328:         os.Exit(1)\n329:     }\n330: }\n331: \n332: // cmd/agentcube-admin/quota.go\n333: func runQuotaSet(namespace string, cfg *QuotaConfig) error {\n334:     clientset, kubeClient, err := getAdminClients()\n335:     if err != nil {\n336:         return err\n337:     }\n338:     \n339:     // Check if namespace exists\n340:     _, err = kubeClient.CoreV1().Namespaces().Get(context.Background(), namespace, metav1.GetOptions{})\n341:     if err != nil {\n342:         return fmt.Errorf(\"namespace %q not found: %w\", namespace, err)\n343:     }\n344:     \n345:     // Create/update resource quota\n346:     quota := &v1.ResourceQuota{\n347:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n348:             Name:      \"agentcube-quota\",\n349:             Namespace: namespace,\n350:         },\n351:         Spec: v1.ResourceQuotaSpec{\n352:             Hard: v1.ResourceList{\n353:                 v1.ResourceRequestsCPU:    resource.MustParse(cfg.DefaultCPU),\n354:                 v1.ResourceRequestsMemory: resource.MustParse(cfg.DefaultMemory),\n355:                 v1.ResourceLimitsCPU:      resource.MustParse(cfg.MaxCPU),\n356:                 v1.ResourceLimitsMemory:   resource.MustParse(cfg.MaxMemory),\n357:             },\n358:         },\n359:     }\n360:     \n361:     _, err = kubeClient.CoreV1().ResourceQuotas(namespace).Create(\n362:         context.Background(), quota, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n363:     if apierrors.IsAlreadyExists(err) {\n364:         _, err = kubeClient.CoreV1().ResourceQuotas(namespace).Update(\n365:             context.Background(), quota, metav1.UpdateOptions{})\n366:     }\n367:     \n368:     return err\n369: }\n370: ```\n371: \n372: ### agentcube-shell - Interactive Shell\n373: \n374: ```go\n375: // cmd/agentcube-shell/main.go\n376: func main() {\n377:     rootCmd := &cobra.Command{\n378:         Use:   \"agentcube-shell\",\n379:         Short: \"AgentCube Interactive Shell for sandbox access\",\n380:     }\n381:     \n382:     rootCmd.PersistentFlags().String(\"kubeconfig\", \"\", \"path to kubeconfig\")\n383:     rootCmd.PersistentFlags().String(\"namespace\", \"default\", \"namespace\")\n384:     rootCmd.PersistentFlags().Duration(\"timeout\", 30*time.Minute, \"session timeout\")\n385:     \n386:     rootCmd.AddCommand(connectCmd, execCmd, cpCmd, portForwardCmd, sessionsCmd)\n387:     \n388:     if err := rootCmd.Execute(); err != nil {\n389:         os.Exit(1)\n390:     }\n391: }\n392: \n393: // cmd/agentcube-shell/connect.go\n394: func runConnect(sandboxName string, cfg *SessionConfig) error {\n395:     clientset, kubeClient, restConfig := getShellClients()\n396:     \n397:     // Get sandbox\n398:     ci, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(cfg.Namespace).Get(\n399:         context.Background(), sandboxName, metav1.GetOptions{})\n400:     if err != nil {\n401:         return err\n402:     }\n403:     \n404:     if ci.Status.Phase != runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterRunning {\n405:         return fmt.Errorf(\"sandbox is not running (phase: %s)\", ci.Status.Phase)\n406:     }\n407:     \n408:     // Get pod name from status\n409:     podName := ci.Status.PodName\n410:     if podName == \"\" {\n411:         return fmt.Errorf(\"sandbox pod name not available\")\n412:     }\n413:     \n414:     // Establish SPDY connection for exec\n415:     req := kubeClient.CoreV1().RESTClient().Post().\n416:         Resource(\"pods\").\n417:         Name(podName).\n418:         Namespace(cfg.Namespace).\n419:         SubResource(\"exec\").\n420:         Param(\"container\", \"sandbox\").\n421:         Param(\"stdin\", \"true\").\n422:         Param(\"stdout\", \"true\").\n423:         Param(\"stderr\", \"true\").\n424:         Param(\"tty\", \"true\").\n425:         Param(\"command\", cfg.ShellType)\n426:     \n427:     executor, err := remotecommand.NewSPDYExecutor(restConfig, \"POST\", req.URL())\n428:     if err != nil {\n429:         return err\n430:     }\n431:     \n432:     // Attach terminal\n433:     return executor.StreamWithContext(context.Background(), remotecommand.StreamOptions{\n434:         Stdin:  os.Stdin,\n435:         Stdout: os.Stdout,\n436:         Stderr: os.Stderr,\n437:         Tty:    true,\n438:     })\n439: }\n440: ```\n441: \n442: ### agentcube-proxy - API Proxy\n443: \n444: ```go\n445: // cmd/agentcube-proxy/main.go\n446: func main() {\n447:     rootCmd := &cobra.Command{\n448:         Use:   \"agentcube-proxy\",\n449:         Short: \"AgentCube API Proxy for local port forwarding\",\n450:     }\n451:     \n452:     rootCmd.PersistentFlags().String(\"kubeconfig\", \"\", \"path to kubeconfig\")\n453:     rootCmd.PersistentFlags().String(\"listen\", \"127.0.0.1\", \"listen address\")\n454:     rootCmd.PersistentFlags().Int(\"port\", 8080, \"listen port\")\n455:     \n456:     rootCmd.AddCommand(startCmd, statusCmd, stopCmd)\n457:     \n458:     if err := rootCmd.Execute(); err != nil {\n459:         os.Exit(1)\n460:     }\n461: }\n462: \n463: // cmd/agentcube-proxy/start.go\n464: func runProxy(opts *ProxyConfig) error {\n465:     clientset, restConfig := getProxyClients()\n466:     \n467:     // Build transport with auth\n468:     transport, err := rest.TransportFor(restConfig)\n469:     if err != nil {\n470:         return err\n471:     }\n472:     \n473:     // Create reverse proxy\n474:     targetURL := restConfig.Host\n475:     proxy := httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy(targetURL)\n476:     proxy.Transport = transport\n477:     \n478:     // Add authentication header\n479:     baseHandler := http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n480:         if opts.AuthToken != \"\" {\n481:             if token := r.Header.Get(\"Authorization\"); token != \"Bearer \"+opts.AuthToken {\n482:                 http.Error(w, \"unauthorized\", http.StatusUnauthorized)\n483:                 return\n484:             }\n485:         }\n486:         proxy.ServeHTTP(w, r)\n487:     })\n488:     \n489:     server := &http.Server{\n490:         Addr:    fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%d\", opts.ListenAddress, opts.ListenPort),\n491:         Handler: baseHandler,\n492:     }\n493:     \n494:     if opts.TLS {\n495:         return server.ListenAndServeTLS(opts.TLSCert, opts.TLSKey)\n496:     }\n497:     \n498:     return server.ListenAndServe()\n499: }\n500: ```\n501: \n502: ## Error Handling\n503: \n504: ### Error Categories\n505: \n506: ```go\n507: // pkg/cliutil/errors.go\n508: type CLIError struct {\n509:     Code    string\n510:     Message string\n511:     Err     error\n512: }\n513: \n514: func (e *CLIError) Error() string {\n515:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"[%s] %s: %v\", e.Code, e.Message, e.Err)\n516: }\n517: \n518: // Error codes\n519: const (\n520:     ErrConfigNotFound   = \"CONFIG_NOT_FOUND\"\n521:     ErrAuthFailed       = \"AUTH_FAILED\"\n522:     ErrResourceNotFound = \"RESOURCE_NOT_FOUND\"\n523:     ErrResourceExists   = \"RESOURCE_EXISTS\"\n524:     ErrInvalidInput     = \"INVALID_INPUT\"\n525:     ErrTimeout          = \"TIMEOUT\"\n526:     ErrInternal         = \"INTERNAL\"\n527: )\n528: \n529: func NewCLIError(code, msg string, err error) *CLIError {\n530:     return &CLIError{Code: code, Message: msg, Err: err}\n531: }\n532: \n533: func WrapError(err error, msg string) *CLIError {\n534:     return &CLIError{Code: ErrInternal, Message: msg, Err: err}\n535: }\n536: ```\n537: \n538: ### Error Handling Strategy\n539: \n540: 1. **Configuration errors**: Clear message + path to fix\n541: 2. **API errors**: Show resource name, namespace, and API response\n542: 3. **Validation errors**: List all validation failures\n543: 4. **Timeout errors**: Suggest increasing timeout or checking resource status\n544: 5. **Internal errors**: Include correlation ID for debugging\n545: \n546: ```go\n547: func handleError(err error) {\n548:     var cliErr *CLIError\n549:     if errors.As(err, &cliErr) {\n550:         fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"Error %s: %s\\n\", cliErr.Code, cliErr.Message)\n551:         if cliErr.Err != nil {\n552:             fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"Caused by: %v\\n\", cliErr.Err)\n553:         }\n554:         os.Exit(1)\n555:     }\n556:     \n557:     // Handle Kubernetes API errors\n558:     if apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n559:         fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"Error: resource not found\\n\")\n560:     } else if apierrors.IsAlreadyExists(err) {\n561:         fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"Error: resource already exists\\n\")\n562:     } else if apierrors.IsForbidden(err) {\n563:         fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"Error: permission denied\\n\")\n564:     } else {\n565:         fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"Error: %v\\n\", err)\n566:     }\n567:     os.Exit(1)\n568: }\n569: ```\n570: \n571: ## Testing Strategy\n572: \n573: ### Unit Tests\n574: \n575: ```go\n576: // cmd/agentcube/sandbox_test.go\n577: func TestRunSandboxCreate(t *testing.T) {\n578:     tests := []struct {\n579:         name    string\n580:         opts    *SandboxOptions\n581:         wantErr bool\n582:     }{\n583:         {\n584:             name: \"valid options\",\n585:             opts: &SandboxOptions{\n586:                 Name:        \"test-sandbox\",\n587:                 Namespace:   \"default\",\n588:                 RuntimeType: \"jupyter\",\n589:             },\n590:             wantErr: false,\n591:         },\n592:         {\n593:             name: \"invalid runtime type\",\n594:             opts: &SandboxOptions{\n595:                 Name:        \"test-sandbox\",\n596:                 RuntimeType: \"invalid\",\n597:             },\n598:             wantErr: true,\n599:         },\n600:     }\n601:     \n602:     for _, tt := range tests {\n603:         t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n604:             // Use fake clientset\n605:             clientset := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n606:             err := runSandboxCreateWithClient(tt.opts, clientset)\n607:             if (err != nil) != tt.wantErr {\n608:                 t.Errorf(\"runSandboxCreate() error = %v, wantErr %v\", err, tt.wantErr)\n609:             }\n610:         })\n611:     }\n612: }\n613: ```\n614: \n615: ### Integration Tests\n616: \n617: ```go\n618: // test/integration/cli_test.go\n619: func TestSandboxCreateGetDelete(t *testing.T) {\n620:     // Skip if no cluster available\n621:     if testing.Short() {\n622:         t.Skip(\"skipping integration test\")\n623:     }\n624:     \n625:     // Create test namespace\n626:     ns := createTestNamespace(t)\n627:     defer deleteTestNamespace(t, ns)\n628:     \n629:     // Create sandbox via CLI\n630:     cmd := exec.Command(\"agentcube\", \"sandbox\", \"create\", \"test-sandbox\",\n631:         \"--namespace\", ns, \"--runtime\", \"jupyter\")\n632:     output, err := cmd.CombinedOutput()\n633:     if err != nil {\n634:         t.Fatalf(\"sandbox create failed: %v\\n%s\", err, output)\n635:     }\n636:     \n637:     // Get sandbox\n638:     cmd = exec.Command(\"agentcube\", \"sandbox\", \"get\", \"test-sandbox\",\n639:         \"--namespace\", ns, \"-o\", \"json\")\n640:     output, err = cmd.CombinedOutput()\n641:     if err != nil {\n642:         t.Fatalf(\"sandbox get failed: %v\\n%s\", err, output)\n643:     }\n644:     \n645:     // Delete sandbox\n646:     cmd = exec.Command(\"agentcube\", \"sandbox\", \"delete\", \"test-sandbox\",\n647:         \"--namespace\", ns)\n648:     output, err = cmd.CombinedOutput()\n649:     if err != nil {\n650:         t.Fatalf(\"sandbox delete failed: %v\\n%s\", err, output)\n651:     }\n652: }\n653: ```\n654: \n655: ### E2E Tests\n656: \n657: ```go\n658: // test/e2e/cli_e2e_test.go\n659: func TestFullWorkflow(t *testing.T) {\n660:     // Full workflow: create -> verify -> exec -> delete\n661:     ctx := context.Background()\n662:     \n663:     // Create\n664:     err := runAgentcube(ctx, \"sandbox\", \"create\", \"e2e-test\", \"--runtime\", \"python\")\n665:     require.NoError(t, err)\n666:     \n667:     // Wait for running\n668:     require.NoError(t, waitForSandboxRunning(ctx, \"e2e-test\"))\n669:     \n670:     // Execute command\n671:     output, err := runAgentcubeShell(ctx, \"exec\", \"e2e-test\", \"python\", \"-c\", \"print('hello')\")\n672:     require.NoError(t, err)\n673:     assert.Contains(t, output, \"hello\")\n674:     \n675:     // Cleanup\n676:     runAgentcube(ctx, \"sandbox\", \"delete\", \"e2e-test\", \"--force\")\n677: }\n678: ```\n679: \n680: ## File Index\n681: \n682: | Path | Role |\n683: |------|------|\n684: | `cmd/agentcube/main.go` | Main CLI entry point |\n685: | `cmd/agentcube/sandbox.go` | Sandbox subcommands |\n686: | `cmd/agentcube/runtime.go` | Runtime subcommands |\n687: | `cmd/agentcube/config.go` | Configuration commands |\n688: | `cmd/agentcube-admin/main.go` | Admin CLI entry point |\n689: | `cmd/agentcube-admin/quota.go` | Quota management |\n690: | `cmd/agentcube-admin/health.go` | Health checks |\n691: | `cmd/agentcube-admin/cleanup.go` | Cleanup operations |\n692: | `cmd/agentcube-shell/main.go` | Shell CLI entry point |\n693: | `cmd/agentcube-shell/connect.go` | Interactive connect |\n694: | `cmd/agentcube-shell/exec.go` | Remote exec |\n695: | `cmd/agentcube-proxy/main.go` | Proxy CLI entry point |\n696: | `cmd/agentcube-proxy/start.go` | Proxy server |\n697: | `pkg/cliutil/config.go` | Shared config loading |\n698: | `pkg/cliutil/output.go` | Output formatting |\n699: | `pkg/cliutil/errors.go` | Error types |\n700: | `pkg/cliutil/validation.go` | Input validation |\n701: | `test/integration/cli_test.go` | Integration tests |\n702: | `test/e2e/cli_e2e_test.go` | E2E tests |\n703: \n704: ## Build & Installation\n705: \n706: ### Makefile Targets\n707: \n708: ```makefile\n709: # Build all binaries\n710: build-cli:\n711:     go build -o bin/agentcube ./cmd/agentcube\n712:     go build -o bin/agentcube-admin ./cmd/agentcube-admin\n713:     go build -o bin/agentcube-shell ./cmd/agentcube-shell\n714:     go build -o bin/agentcube-proxy ./cmd/agentcube-proxy\n715: \n716: # Install to GOPATH\n717: install-cli:\n718:     go install ./cmd/agentcube\n719:     go install ./cmd/agentcube-admin\n720:     go install ./cmd/agentcube-shell\n721:     go install ./cmd/agentcube-proxy\n722: \n723: # Cross-compile\n724: build-all-platforms:\n725:     GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/linux/amd64/agentcube ./cmd/agentcube\n726:     GOOS=darwin GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/darwin/amd64/agentcube ./cmd/agentcube\n727:     GOOS=windows GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/windows/amd64/agentcube.exe ./cmd/agentcube\n728: ```\n729: \n730: ### Release Artifacts\n731: \n732: - `agentcube-linux-amd64`, `agentcube-darwin-amd64`, `agentcube-windows-amd64.exe`\n733: - `agentcube-admin-linux-amd64`, etc.\n734: - `agentcube-shell-linux-amd64`, etc.\n735: - `agentcube-proxy-linux-amd64`, etc.\n736: - Shell completion scripts: `agentcube-completion.bash`, `agentcube-completion.zsh`\n\n(End of file - total 736 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Design: AR-019 CLI Binary Entry Points\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation for 4 CLI binaries in the agentcube project. These tools provide command-line interfaces for managing agentcube resources and interacting with the Kubernetes API.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Binary Structure\n\n```\ncmd/\n├── agentd/                      # Kubernetes controller (existing)\n│   └── main.go\n├── agentcube/                   # Main CLI - resource management\n│   └── main.go\n├── agentcube-admin/             # Admin CLI - cluster administration\n│   └── main.go\n├── agentcube-shell/             # Interactive shell - sandbox access\n│   └── main.go","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/design.md","time":{"start":1775878888335,"end":1775878888367}}}}
