{"type":"text","timestamp":1775878906309,"sessionID":"ses_2855f1963ffebvWWhivqMrbUXq","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa19c7d001YIsmeMeUywiez1","messageID":"msg_d7aa18f7f001yvBkIyrzZBkFR5","sessionID":"ses_2855f1963ffebvWWhivqMrbUXq","type":"text","text":"Now I have all the information I need to write a comprehensive design.md for AR-030. Let me create the design document following the established pattern from other design docs in the project:","time":{"start":1775878906308,"end":1775878906308}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879030802,"sessionID":"ses_2855f1963ffebvWWhivqMrbUXq","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa1a1c6001YTTTkBEr5hRcpn","messageID":"msg_d7aa18f7f001yvBkIyrzZBkFR5","sessionID":"ses_2855f1963ffebvWWhivqMrbUXq","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_ea56f345bcd04186ab924d4a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/design.md","content":"# Design: AR-030 Helm Chart Templates and Values\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation for the AgentCube Helm chart (`manifests/charts/base`). The chart packages and deploys all AgentCube control plane components including Router, WorkloadManager, and optional Volcano Agent Scheduler with support for multi-environment configurations.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Chart Structure\n\n```\nmanifests/charts/base/\n├── Chart.yaml                          # Chart metadata (apiVersion, name, version)\n├── values.yaml                         # Configuration values tree\n├── .helmignore                         # Packaging exclusion patterns\n├── crds/\n│   ├── agentruntime.yaml               # AgentRuntime CRD (existing)\n│   └── codeinterpreter.yaml            # CodeInterpreter CRD (new)\n└── templates/\n    ├── _helpers.tpl                    # Template helper functions\n    ├── redis-secret.yaml               # Redis password Secret\n    ├── workloadmanager.yaml            # WorkloadManager Deployment + Service\n    ├── agentcube-router.yaml           # Router Deployment + Service\n    ├── rbac/\n    │   └── workloadmanager.yaml        # WorkloadManager RBAC (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding)\n    ├── rbac-router.yaml                # Optional Router RBAC\n    └── volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml  # Optional Volcano Scheduler\n```\n\n### Component Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Helm Chart (agentcube)                        │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                              │\n                              │ helm install/upgrade\n                              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                   Kubernetes Cluster                             │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌───────────────┐ │\n│  │     Router       │  │ WorkloadManager  │  │   Volcano     │ │\n│  │  Deployment      │  │   Deployment     │  │   Scheduler   │ │\n│  │  + Service       │  │   + Service      │  │  (optional)   │ │\n│  └────────┬─────────┘  └────────┬─────────┘  └───────────────┘ │\n│           │                      │                               │\n│           └──────────┬───────────┘                               │\n│                      │                                           │\n│           ┌──────────▼───────────┐                               │\n│           │   Redis Secret        │                               │\n│           │   (password store)    │                               │\n│           └───────────────────────┘                               │\n│                                                                   │\n│           ┌──────────────────────┐                               │\n│           │   RBAC Resources      │                               │\n│           │   (SA, Role, Binding) │                               │\n│           └───────────────────────┘                               │\n│                                                                   │\n│           ┌──────────────────────┐                               │\n│           │      CRDs             │                               │\n│           │  agentruntimes,       │                               │\n│           │  codeinterpreters     │                               │\n│           └───────────────────────┘                               │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Integration Points\n\n- **Redis**: External dependency for session storage (address/password from values)\n- **Volcano Scheduler**: Optional component for advanced scheduling\n- **RBAC**: WorkloadManager requires cluster-wide permissions; Router RBAC is optional\n- **CRDs**: AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Chart.yaml Metadata\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nname: agentcube\ndescription: A Helm chart for AgentCube\nversion: 0.1.0\nappVersion: \"1.0.0\"\nkeywords:\n  - agent\n  - sandbox\n  - kubernetes\n  - volcano\nmaintainers:\n  - name: Volcano Authors\n    email: volcano-sh@googlegroups.com\nhome: https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\nsources:\n  - https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n```\n\n### values.yaml Configuration Tree\n\n```yaml\n# Global settings\nimagePullSecrets: []\nnameOverride: \"\"\nfullnameOverride: \"\"\n\n# Redis configuration (required)\nredis:\n  addr: \"\"           # Required: Redis address (e.g., \"redis.default.svc.cluster.local:6379\")\n  password: \"\"       # Optional: Redis password for authentication\n\n# Router component\nrouter:\n  replicas: 1\n  image:\n    repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router\n    pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n    tag: \"latest\"\n  service:\n    type: ClusterIP\n    port: 8080\n    targetPort: 8080\n  resources:\n    limits:\n      cpu: 500m\n      memory: 512Mi\n    requests:\n      cpu: 100m\n      memory: 128Mi\n  config: {}                      # Additional container configuration\n  extraEnv: []                    # Additional environment variables\n  serviceAccountName: \"\"          # Empty for default/auto-generated\n  rbac:\n    create: false                 # Disable RBAC by default\n\n# WorkloadManager component\nworkloadmanager:\n  replicas: 1\n  image:\n    repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager\n    pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n    tag: \"latest\"\n  service:\n    type: ClusterIP\n    port: 8080\n  resources:\n    limits:\n      cpu: 500m\n      memory: 512Mi\n    requests:\n      cpu: 100m\n      memory: 128Mi\n  extraEnv: []                    # Additional environment variables\n\n# Volcano Scheduler (optional)\nvolcano:\n  scheduler:\n    enabled: false                # Disabled by default\n    replicas: 1\n    image:\n      repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler\n      pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n      tag: \"latest\"\n```\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Component | Description | Source |\n|----------|-----------|-------------|--------|\n| `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | All | Namespace from downward API | `fieldRef: metadata.namespace` |\n| `REDIS_ADDR` | Router, WorkloadManager | Redis connection address | `{{ .Values.redis.addr }}` |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Router, WorkloadManager | Redis authentication | `Secret {{ .Release.Name }}-redis` key `password` |\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Router | Workload Manager endpoint | Constructed: `http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}` |\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Template Contracts\n\n#### WorkloadManager Deployment\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: apps/v1\nkind: Deployment\nmetadata:\n  name: workloadmanager\n  namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n  labels:\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: workloadmanager\n    app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}\nspec:\n  replicas: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.replicas }}\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: workloadmanager\n  template:\n    metadata:\n      labels:\n        app: workloadmanager\n    spec:\n      serviceAccountName: workloadmanager\n      containers:\n      - name: workloadmanager\n        image: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.tag }}\n        imagePullPolicy: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy }}\n        args:\n        - --port={{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n        - --runtime-class-name=\n        env:\n        - name: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\n          valueFrom:\n            fieldRef:\n              fieldPath: metadata.namespace\n        - name: REDIS_ADDR\n          value: {{ .Values.redis.addr }}\n        - name: REDIS_PASSWORD\n          valueFrom:\n            secretKeyRef:\n              name: {{ .Release.Name }}-redis\n              key: password\n        - name: {{ .name }}\n          value: {{ .value }}\n        # ... extraEnv injected here\n        ports:\n        - name: http\n          containerPort: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n          protocol: TCP\n        livenessProbe:\n          httpGet:\n            path: /health\n            port: http\n          initialDelaySeconds: 10\n          periodSeconds: 10\n        readinessProbe:\n          httpGet:\n            path: /health\n            port: http\n          initialDelaySeconds: 5\n          periodSeconds: 5\n        resources: {{ toYaml .Values.workloadmanager.resources | nindent 10 }}\n```\n\n#### Router Deployment\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: apps/v1\nkind: Deployment\nmetadata:\n  name: agentcube-router\n  namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n  labels:\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube-router\n    app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}\nspec:\n  replicas: {{ .Values.router.replicas }}\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: agentcube-router\n  template:\n    metadata:\n      labels:\n        app: agentcube-router\n    spec:\n      {{- if .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n      serviceAccountName: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n      {{- end }}\n      containers:\n      - name: agentcube-router\n        image: {{ .Values.router.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.router.image.tag }}\n        imagePullPolicy: {{ .Values.router.image.pullPolicy }}\n        args:\n        - --port={{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}\n        - --debug\n        env:\n        - name: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\n          valueFrom:\n            fieldRef:\n              fieldPath: metadata.namespace\n        - name: REDIS_ADDR\n          value: {{ .Values.redis.addr }}\n        - name: REDIS_PASSWORD\n          valueFrom:\n            secretKeyRef:\n              name: {{ .Release.Name }}-redis\n              key: password\n        - name: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n          value: \"http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\"\n        # ... extraEnv injected here\n        ports:\n        - name: http\n          containerPort: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}\n          protocol: TCP\n        livenessProbe:\n          httpGet:\n            path: /health/live\n            port: http\n          initialDelaySeconds: 1\n          periodSeconds: 2\n        readinessProbe:\n          httpGet:\n            path: /health/ready\n            port: http\n          initialDelaySeconds: 1\n          periodSeconds: 2\n        resources: {{ toYaml .Values.router.resources | nindent 10 }}\n```\n\n#### WorkloadManager RBAC\n\n```yaml\n# ServiceAccount\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ServiceAccount\nmetadata:\n  name: workloadmanager\n  namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n\n# ClusterRole\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: ClusterRole\nmetadata:\n  name: workloadmanager\nrules:\n# Sandbox management\n- apiGroups: [\"agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n  resources: [\"sandboxes\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n\n# Extension resources\n- apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n  resources: [\"sandboxclaims\", \"sandboxtemplates\", \"sandboxwarmpools\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n\n# Warm pool status update\n- apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n  resources: [\"sandboxwarmpools/status\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n\n# CodeInterpreter management\n- apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n  resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n- apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n  resources: [\"codeinterpreters/status\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n- apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n  resources: [\"codeinterpreters/finalizers\"]\n  verbs: [\"update\"]\n\n# AgentRuntime management\n- apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n  resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n- apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n  resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\"]\n  verbs: [\"update\", \"patch\"]\n\n# Pod read access\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources: [\"pods\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n\n# Token review for authentication\n- apiGroups: [\"authentication.k8s.io\"]\n  resources: [\"tokenreviews\"]\n  verbs: [\"create\"]\n\n# Secret management\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources: [\"secrets\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n\n# ClusterRoleBinding\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: ClusterRoleBinding\nmetadata:\n  name: workloadmanager\nroleRef:\n  apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n  kind: ClusterRole\n  name: workloadmanager\nsubjects:\n- kind: ServiceAccount\n  name: workloadmanager\n  namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n```\n\n#### Router RBAC (Optional)\n\nRendered only when `router.rbac.create: true`:\n\n```yaml\n# ServiceAccount\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ServiceAccount\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n  namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n\n# Role (namespace-scoped)\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: Role\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n  namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\nrules:\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources: [\"secrets\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n\n# RoleBinding\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: RoleBinding\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n  namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\nroleRef:\n  apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n  kind: Role\n  name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\nsubjects:\n- kind: ServiceAccount\n  name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n  namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n```\n\n#### Volcano Agent Scheduler (Optional)\n\nRendered only when `volcano.scheduler.enabled: true`:\n\n```yaml\n# ServiceAccount\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ServiceAccount\nmetadata:\n  name: volcano-agent-scheduler\n\n# ConfigMap\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ConfigMap\nmetadata:\n  name: volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap\ndata:\n  agent-scheduler.conf: |\n    actions: \"allocate\"\n    tiers:\n    - plugins:\n      - name: predicates\n      - name: nodeorder\n\n# ClusterRole with comprehensive scheduling permissions\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: ClusterRole\nmetadata:\n  name: volcano-agent-scheduler\nrules:\n# CRD management\n- apiGroups: [\"apiextensions.k8s.io\"]\n  resources: [\"customresourcedefinitions\"]\n  verbs: [\"create\", \"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"delete\"]\n\n# Core resources\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources: [\"events\", \"pods\", \"pods/status\", \"pods/binding\"]\n  verbs: [\"create\", \"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n# ... (additional pod-related permissions)\n\n# Deployment\napiVersion: apps/v1\nkind: Deployment\nmetadata:\n  name: volcano-agent-scheduler\nspec:\n  replicas: {{ .Values.volcano.scheduler.replicas }}\n  template:\n    spec:\n      serviceAccountName: volcano-agent-scheduler\n      containers:\n      - name: volcano-agent-scheduler\n        image: {{ .Values.volcano.scheduler.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.volcano.scheduler.image.tag }}\n        args:\n        - --scheduler-name=agent-scheduler\n        - --config=/config/agent-scheduler.conf\n        securityContext:\n          runAsNonRoot: true\n          runAsUser: 1000\n        volumeMounts:\n        - name: config\n          mountPath: /config\n        - name: empty\n          mountPath: /emptydir\n      volumes:\n      - name: config\n        configMap:\n          name: volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap\n      - name: empty\n        emptyDir: {}\n```\n\n### CRD Definitions\n\n#### AgentRuntime CRD\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: apiextensions.k8s.io/v1\nkind: CustomResourceDefinition\nmetadata:\n  name: agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\nspec:\n  group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n  names:\n    kind: AgentRuntime\n    plural: agentruntimes\n    shortNames: [ar]\n    singular: agentruntime\n  scope: Namespaced\n  versions:\n  - name: v1alpha1\n    served: true\n    storage: true\n    additionalPrinterColumns:\n    - name: NAME\n      type: string\n      jsonPath: .metadata.name\n    - name: PHASE\n      type: string\n      jsonPath: .status.phase\n    - name: SANDBOX\n      type: string\n      jsonPath: .status.sandboxRef.name\n    - name: AGE\n      type: date\n      jsonPath: .metadata.creationTimestamp\n    schema:\n      openAPIV3Schema:\n        type: object\n        properties:\n          spec:\n            required:\n            - maxSessionDuration\n            - podTemplate\n            - sessionTimeout\n            - targetPort\n            properties:\n              maxSessionDuration:\n                type: string\n                default: \"8h\"\n              sessionTimeout:\n                type: string\n                default: \"15m\"\n              targetPort:\n                type: array\n                items:\n                  type: object\n                  required: [port, protocol]\n                  properties:\n                    port:\n                      type: integer\n                    protocol:\n                      type: string\n                      enum: [HTTP, HTTPS]\n              podTemplate:\n                type: object\n                # Full PodSpec-like schema\n```\n\n#### CodeInterpreter CRD\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: apiextensions.k8s.io/v1\nkind: CustomResourceDefinition\nmetadata:\n  name: codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\nspec:\n  group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n  names:\n    kind: CodeInterpreter\n    plural: codeinterpreters\n    shortNames: [ci]\n    singular: codeinterpreter\n  scope: Namespaced\n  versions:\n  - name: v1alpha1\n    served: true\n    storage: true\n    subresources:\n      status: {}\n    schema:\n      openAPIV3Schema:\n        type: object\n        properties:\n          spec:\n            required: [template]\n            properties:\n              authMode:\n                type: string\n                enum: [picod, none]\n                default: picod\n              maxSessionDuration:\n                type: string\n                default: \"8h\"\n              sessionTimeout:\n                type: string\n                default: \"15m\"\n              warmPoolSize:\n                type: integer\n                format: int32\n              template:\n                type: object\n                # Container template schema\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Chart Validation Errors\n\n| Error | Exit Code | Message |\n|-------|-----------|---------|\n| Chart validation failure | 1 | `helm lint failed: {detail}` |\n| Template render failure | 1 | `helm template failed: {detail}` |\n| CRD installation failure | 1 | `Failed to install CRD: {detail}` |\n| Redis address not provided | 1 | `redis.addr is required in values` |\n| Invalid YAML syntax | 1 | `YAML parse error in {file}: {detail}` |\n\n### Runtime Errors\n\n| Error | Component | Recovery |\n|-------|-----------|----------|\n| Redis connection refused | Router, WorkloadManager | Retry with exponential backoff |\n| Invalid Redis password | Router, WorkloadManager | Log error, fail health check |\n| RBAC permission denied | WorkloadManager | Log error, fail reconciliation |\n| CRD not found | All components | Fail startup, require manual CRD install |\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n**Location**: `manifests/charts/base/tests/` (to be created)\n\n```yaml\n# tests/workloadmanager_test.yaml\nsuite: WorkloadManager Deployment tests\ntests:\n  - it: creates Deployment with correct metadata\n    asserts:\n      - hasDocuments:\n          count: 1\n        documentIndex: 0\n        isKind:\n          of: Deployment\n      - equal:\n          path: metadata.name\n          value: workloadmanager\n\n  - it: sets replicas from values\n    set:\n      workloadmanager.replicas: 3\n    asserts:\n      - equal:\n          path: spec.replicas\n          value: 3\n\n  - it: injects correct environment variables\n    asserts:\n      - contains:\n          path: spec.template.spec.containers[0].env\n          content:\n            name: REDIS_ADDR\n            value: \"redis.default.svc.cluster.local:6379\"\n\n  - it: configures liveness probe correctly\n    asserts:\n      - equal:\n          path: spec.template.spec.containers[0].livenessProbe.httpGet.path\n          value: /health\n      - equal:\n          path: spec.template.spec.containers[0].livenessProbe.initialDelaySeconds\n          value: 10\n\n  - it: applies resource limits from values\n    set:\n      workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu: 1000m\n      workloadmanager.resources.limits.memory: 1Gi\n    asserts:\n      - equal:\n          path: spec.template.spec.containers[0].resources.limits.cpu\n          value: 1000m\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n**Command**: `helm template test manifests/charts/base`\n\nVerify:\n1. All templates render without errors\n2. Generated YAML is valid\n3. Conditional resources respect flags\n4. Values overrides work correctly\n\n**Command**: `helm lint manifests/charts/base`\n\nVerify:\n1. No linting errors or warnings\n2. Chart structure is valid\n3. All required files present\n\n### E2E Tests\n\n**Scenario**: Full chart installation in Kind cluster\n\n```bash\n# Create Kind cluster\nkind create cluster --name agentcube-e2e\n\n# Install chart\nhelm install agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n  --namespace agentcube \\\n  --create-namespace \\\n  --set redis.addr=\"redis.agentcube.svc.cluster.local:6379\" \\\n  --set redis.password=\"\" \\\n  --wait\n\n# Verify deployments are ready\nkubectl wait deployment/workloadmanager --for=condition=Available --namespace=agentcube --timeout=2m\nkubectl wait deployment/agentcube-router --for=condition=Available --namespace=agentcube --timeout=2m\n\n# Verify services are created\nkubectl get svc -n agentcube\n\n# Test with optional components\nhelm upgrade agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n  --namespace agentcube \\\n  --set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true \\\n  --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n  --wait\n\n# Verify optional components\nkubectl wait deployment/volcano-agent-scheduler --for=condition=Available --namespace=agentcube --timeout=2m\nkubectl get clusterrole/workloadmanager\nkubectl get role/agentcube-router --namespace=agentcube\n\n# Cleanup\nkind delete cluster --name agentcube-e2e\n```\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| Helm | ≥3.0.0 | Chart packaging and deployment |\n| Kubernetes | ≥1.21 | API compatibility |\n| Redis | Any | External dependency (session storage) |\n| Volcano | Optional | Advanced scheduling (if enabled) |\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\nmanifests/\n└── charts/\n    └── base/\n        ├── Chart.yaml                    # REQUIRED: Chart metadata\n        ├── values.yaml                   # REQUIRED: Default configuration\n        ├── .helmignore                   # REQUIRED: Packaging exclusions\n        ├── crds/\n        │   ├── agentruntime.yaml         # EXISTING: AgentRuntime CRD\n        │   └── codeinterpreter.yaml      # NEW: CodeInterpreter CRD\n        └── templates/\n            ├── _helpers.tpl              # Helper templates\n            ├── redis-secret.yaml         # Redis password Secret\n            ├── workloadmanager.yaml      # WorkloadManager Deployment + Service\n            ├── agentcube-router.yaml     # Router Deployment + Service\n            ├── rbac/\n            │   └── workloadmanager.yaml  # WorkloadManager RBAC\n            ├── rbac-router.yaml          # Optional Router RBAC\n            └── volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml  # Optional Volcano Scheduler\n```\n\n## Multi-Environment Support\n\n### Development Environment\n\n```yaml\n# values-dev.yaml\nrouter:\n  replicas: 1\n  resources:\n    limits:\n      cpu: 250m\n      memory: 256Mi\n    requests:\n      cpu: 50m\n      memory: 64Mi\n\nworkloadmanager:\n  replicas: 1\n  resources:\n    limits:\n      cpu: 250m\n      memory: 256Mi\n    requests:\n      cpu: 50m\n      memory: 64Mi\n\nvolcano:\n  scheduler:\n    enabled: false\n```\n\n### Production Environment\n\n```yaml\n# values-prod.yaml\nrouter:\n  replicas: 3\n  resources:\n    limits:\n      cpu: 1000m\n      memory: 1Gi\n    requests:\n      cpu: 200m\n      memory: 256Mi\n\nworkloadmanager:\n  replicas: 2\n  resources:\n    limits:\n      cpu: 1000m\n      memory: 1Gi\n    requests:\n      cpu: 200m\n      memory: 256Mi\n\nvolcano:\n  scheduler:\n    enabled: true\n    replicas: 2\n```\n\n### Usage\n\n```bash\n# Development\nhelm install agentcube manifests/charts/base -f values-dev.yaml \\\n  --set redis.addr=redis-dev:6379\n\n# Production\nhelm install agentcube manifests/charts/base -f values-prod.yaml \\\n  --set redis.addr=redis-prod:6379\n\n# Custom image registry\nhelm install agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n  --set router.image.repository=myregistry.com/agentcube-router \\\n  --set workloadmanager.image.repository=myregistry.com/workloadmanager\n```\n\n## Acceptance Checklist\n\n- [ ] `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` — Chart metadata with correct apiVersion, name, version\n- [ ] `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` — Complete configuration tree for all components\n- [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` — Deployment + Service with correct env/probes\n- [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` — Deployment + Service with WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n- [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` — ServiceAccount + ClusterRole + ClusterRoleBinding\n- [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` — Conditional Router RBAC\n- [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` — Conditional Volcano Scheduler\n- [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/redis-secret.yaml` — Redis password Secret\n- [ ] `manifests/charts/base/crds/agentruntime.yaml` — AgentRuntime CRD (existing, verify completeness)\n- [ ] `manifests/charts/base/crds/codeinterpreter.yaml` — CodeInterpreter CRD (new)\n- [ ] `manifests/charts/base/.helmignore` — Ignore patterns for packaging\n- [ ] `helm lint` passes without errors\n- [ ] `helm template` generates valid YAML\n- [ ] `helm install` succeeds in Kind cluster\n- [ ] Optional components render correctly when enabled/disabled\n- [ ] Values overrides work correctly for multi-environment support\n\n## Open Questions\n\n1. **External Redis Operator Integration**: Should the chart support automatic Redis provisioning via Redis Operator (e.g., Spotahome, OperatorHub)?\n\n2. **Monitoring and Logging**: Should Prometheus scrape annotations, ServiceMonitor CRs, and Fluentd/ELK integration be included in the chart?\n\n3. **Multi-Cluster Deployment**: Should the chart support deployment across multiple Kubernetes clusters with shared Redis backend?\n\n4. **Default Values for Development**: Should the chart include a `values-dev.yaml` file with development-appropriate defaults out of the box?\n\n5. **Ingress Configuration**: Should an Ingress resource be added for external access to Router and WorkloadManager services?\n\n6. **Pod Disruption Budgets**: Should PDBs be configured for production deployments to ensure availability during node maintenance?\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/charts/base/crds/agentruntime.yaml\">\nERROR [126:48] Nested mappings are not allowed in compact mappings\nERROR [138:48] Nested mappings are not allowed in compact mappings\n</diagnostics>","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/charts/base/crds/agentruntime.yaml":[{"range":{"start":{"line":125,"character":47},"end":{"line":125,"character":85}},"message":"Nested mappings are not allowed in compact mappings","severity":1,"code":0,"source":"YAML"},{"range":{"start":{"line":137,"character":47},"end":{"line":137,"character":77}},"message":"Nested mappings are not allowed in compact mappings","severity":1,"code":0,"source":"YAML"}]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/design.md","time":{"start":1775879030784,"end":1775879030797}}}}
